1
00:01:38,167 --> 00:01:40,133
HEY, MISS.

2
00:01:43,067 --> 00:01:44,667
ER, UH, MISS.

3
00:01:44,734 --> 00:01:47,701
I THINK YOU CAN SEE BETTER
FROM WAY UP HERE.

4
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:52,234
CAN Y'ALL HEAR ME?

5
00:01:54,467 --> 00:01:57,267
WE CAN SEE ALL RIGHT
FROM A-WAY DOWN HERE.

6
00:01:57,334 --> 00:01:58,601
HA HA HA!

7
00:01:58,667 --> 00:02:00,334
HA HA! DOESN'T
SEEM LIKE IT.

8
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:01,367
YOU BETTER
COME ON UP.

9
00:02:01,434 --> 00:02:02,701
DON'T PAY ANY
ATTENTION TO HIM.

10
00:02:02,767 --> 00:02:04,400
HE'S JUST PRETENDING
HE DOESN'T REMEMBER ME.

11
00:02:04,467 --> 00:02:06,000
<i>OH, I REMEMBER YOU,
ALL RIGHT.</i>

12
00:02:06,067 --> 00:02:07,934
HE DOES, HUH? BETTER COME ON UP, HUH?

13
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:09,667
ALL RIGHT.
THANKS.

14
00:02:09,734 --> 00:02:12,200
COME ON, TED, UNBEND AND
HELP THE LITTLE LADY UP.

15
00:02:12,267 --> 00:02:13,234
OOH!

16
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:14,234
CAREFUL, NOW.

17
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:15,234
WAIT, NOW!

18
00:02:15,300 --> 00:02:16,601
OOP!

19
00:02:16,667 --> 00:02:17,634
OH, THANKS.

20
00:02:17,701 --> 00:02:18,868
AHH.
THERE YOU ARE.

21
00:02:18,934 --> 00:02:21,167
YOU KNOW, TED'S HAD A GRUDGE AGAINST ME

22
00:02:21,234 --> 00:02:22,601
EVER SINCE THE DAY I SHOVED HIM

23
00:02:22,667 --> 00:02:23,968
INTO THE SEVERN RIVER YEARS AGO.

24
00:02:24,033 --> 00:02:25,400
SEVERN?
MM-HMM.

25
00:02:25,467 --> 00:02:26,901
DID YOU LIVE
IN ANNAPOLIS?

26
00:02:26,968 --> 00:02:28,167
WELL, I WAS THERE
WITH MY DAD.

27
00:02:28,234 --> 00:02:29,968
WHEREVER HE WAS STATIONED,
I WAS STUCK THERE, TOO.

28
00:02:30,033 --> 00:02:31,200
THEN YOU'RE NAVY.

29
00:02:31,267 --> 00:02:33,133
NO, BUT MY DAD IS, AND
HIS FATHER BEFORE HIM,

30
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:34,868
HIS FATHER BEFORE HIM,
HIS FATHER BEFORE HIM...

31
00:02:34,934 --> 00:02:37,100
I GET IT. NAVY,
RIGHT DOWN THE LINE.

32
00:02:37,167 --> 00:02:38,868
AH, BUT THE LINE SANK
WHEN IT CAME TO ME.

33
00:02:38,934 --> 00:02:40,868
NO NAVY FOR MINE.

34
00:02:40,934 --> 00:02:43,968
WELL, AS, UH... AS LONG AS
TED DOESN'T SEEM TO BELIEVE

35
00:02:44,033 --> 00:02:46,267
IN THE FORMALITIES
OF INTRODUCTION,

36
00:02:46,334 --> 00:02:47,868
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

37
00:02:47,934 --> 00:02:49,167
I BEGS TO REPORT,
MA'AM,

38
00:02:49,234 --> 00:02:50,367
THAT MY NAME IS
RICHARD MELVILLE III...

39
00:02:50,434 --> 00:02:51,400
OR THE SECOND
OR THE FOURTH.

40
00:02:51,467 --> 00:02:52,400
HAVEN'T FIGURED
IT OUT YET.

41
00:02:52,467 --> 00:02:54,934
ARE YOU ADMIRAL
MELVILLE'S SON?

42
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,334
YOU GOT ME.

43
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,634
YOU DON'T LOOK
LIKE A MELVILLE.

44
00:02:57,701 --> 00:02:59,934
HA HA HA!
WHY NOT?

45
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,100
I DON'T KNOW.

46
00:03:01,167 --> 00:03:03,400
I SUPPOSE IT'S BECAUSE
I JUST COULDN'T PICTURE

47
00:03:03,467 --> 00:03:04,868
A MELVILLE WITHOUT
A UNIFORM.

48
00:03:04,934 --> 00:03:06,567
WHOA, THERE.
YOU SOUND LIKE MY DAD

49
00:03:06,634 --> 00:03:08,467
WHEN HE OPENS UP HIS
FAMILY BROADSIDES ON ME.

50
00:03:08,534 --> 00:03:10,534
I HEAR THAT SO OFTEN.

51
00:03:10,601 --> 00:03:12,200
THERE'S HIS FLAGSHIP
OUT THERE NOW.

52
00:03:15,934 --> 00:03:19,734
WANT TO TAKE A GANDER? A PEEP?

53
00:03:32,667 --> 00:03:36,033
DO YOU GET A KICK OUT OF
THOSE CAST-IRON BATHTUBS?

54
00:03:36,100 --> 00:03:37,367
ARE YOU A NAVY GIRL?

55
00:03:37,434 --> 00:03:40,067
I WAS A NAVY GIRL.

56
00:03:40,133 --> 00:03:42,133
MY FATHER WAS
CAPTAIN BLACKBURN.

57
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:44,701
HE WENT DOWN WITH HIS SHIP IN THE WAR.

58
00:03:44,767 --> 00:03:46,234
OH, I'M SORRY.

59
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:50,467
MY BROTHER JIM WAS A LIEUTENANT
- NAVAL AIR SERVICE.

60
00:03:55,634 --> 00:03:57,234
YES.

61
00:03:57,300 --> 00:04:00,033
NO WONDER YOU THINK I
SHOULD BE WEARING A UNIFORM.

62
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:01,934
NO, I DON'T.

63
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,334
THE NAVY TOOK MY FATHER
AND MY BROTHER,

64
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:05,968
AND MOTHER DIED
BECAUSE SHE THOUGHT

65
00:04:06,033 --> 00:04:08,834
SHE SHOULD BE WITH DAD
ON THE CHINA STATION.

66
00:04:09,868 --> 00:04:12,367
I'VE HAD ENOUGH NAVY
IN MY FAMILY.

67
00:04:14,634 --> 00:04:16,934
WELL, HERE WE ARE
- TWO AGAINST THE NAVY.

68
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,868
MAYBE JUNE'S GOT SOME
REASON FOR WHAT SHE SAYS,

69
00:04:18,934 --> 00:04:21,234
<i>BUT WHAT RIGHT HAVE YOU
GOT TO POOH-POOH THE NAVY?</i>

70
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:23,334
I SUPPOSE YOU'RE
A SUCKER FOR A UNIFORM

71
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:24,667
JUST BECAUSE
YOUR DAD WEARS ONE.

72
00:04:24,734 --> 00:04:26,467
I'M NOT GOING TO TRADE
MY CHANCE TO WEAR ONE

73
00:04:26,534 --> 00:04:28,367
FOR THE PRIVILEGE
OF BEING A CROONER.

74
00:04:29,567 --> 00:04:30,934
NOW, NOW, NOW.
HEH HEH HEH!

75
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,000
YOU KNOW I'M VERY SENSITIVE ABOUT THAT.

76
00:04:33,067 --> 00:04:34,334
I LIKE YOUR MUSIC.

77
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:36,267
DON'T MIND TED.

78
00:04:36,334 --> 00:04:39,200
YOU TWO FIGHT LIKE BROTHER AND
SISTER, OR LIKE YOU WERE MARRIED.

79
00:04:39,267 --> 00:04:43,734
TED'S MY COUSIN. HIS
FATHER SORT OF ADOPTED ME.

80
00:04:43,801 --> 00:04:46,567
OH. WELL, AT LEAST I'M
GLAD YOU'RE NOT MARRIED...

81
00:04:46,634 --> 00:04:47,767
TO HIM.

82
00:04:47,834 --> 00:04:50,901
WE DON'T MARRY FIRST
COUSINS WHERE I COME FROM.

83
00:04:50,968 --> 00:04:52,634
BESIDES,
TED'S GOING NAVY-

84
00:04:52,701 --> 00:04:55,400
GOING TO TRY FOR THE ACADEMY THIS YEAR.

85
00:04:55,467 --> 00:04:57,501
I'D NEVER MARRY
A NAVY MAN.

86
00:04:58,634 --> 00:05:00,501
THAT'S THE BEST NEWS
I'VE HEARD TODAY.

87
00:05:00,567 --> 00:05:01,968
DOES THAT MAKE ME
ELIGIBLE?

88
00:05:05,434 --> 00:05:06,734
DO YOU WANT TO BE?

89
00:05:08,334 --> 00:05:10,067
YOU AND TED COME DOWN
TO THE SKY CLUB TONIGHT,

90
00:05:10,133 --> 00:05:11,234
AND I'LL SWEAR OUT
AN AFFIDAVIT.

91
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:13,100
IF YOU THINK I'D PAY
A $5.00 COVER CHARGE

92
00:05:13,167 --> 00:05:14,667
TO HEAR YOU SING,
YOU'RE CRAZY.

93
00:05:14,734 --> 00:05:17,067
JUST PUT A LITTLE COTTON
IN YOUR EARS, TED.

94
00:05:17,133 --> 00:05:19,934
BRING LITTLE JUNE ALONG, AND I'LL
TREAT YOU TO THE COVER CHARGE.

95
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:21,200
I'LL TREAT YOU
TO A...

96
00:05:21,267 --> 00:05:23,601
OH, GO TAKE A HOP,
SKIP, AND A JUMP.

97
00:05:24,934 --> 00:05:26,100
YOU KNOW, IF FAMILY
INFLUENCE MEANS ANYTHING,

98
00:05:26,167 --> 00:05:27,634
YOU'RE GOING TO
LIKE ME A LOT.

99
00:05:31,133 --> 00:05:33,834
I THINK I'LL TAKE
ANOTHER GANDER.

100
00:06:06,133 --> 00:06:08,133
MY NAME IS RICHARD MELVILLE.
THE ADMIRAL EXPECTS ME.

101
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,901
OH, YES.
THE ADMIRAL IS ON DECK.

102
00:06:12,934 --> 00:06:16,100
WELL...
HELLO, SON.

103
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:17,901
HELLO, DAD. NICE FLEET
YOU BROUGHT HOME WITH YOU.

104
00:06:17,968 --> 00:06:20,100
YOU EVIDENTLY GOT MY TELEGRAM,
OR YOU WOULDN'T BE HERE.

105
00:06:20,167 --> 00:06:22,367
UH-HUH. WELL, HAVE
YOU COME TO A DECISION?

106
00:06:22,434 --> 00:06:23,701
YOU EXPECT ME
TO CHANGE MY MIND?

107
00:06:23,767 --> 00:06:25,267
I SINCERELY HOPE SO.

108
00:06:25,334 --> 00:06:27,767
WELL, I HAVEN'T HAD
ANY REASON TO CHANGE IT.

109
00:06:27,834 --> 00:06:29,767
COME HERE, SON.

110
00:06:29,834 --> 00:06:34,167
DICK, DOESN'T THE SIGHT OF THE
FLEET TODAY BRING ANY RESPONSE,

111
00:06:34,234 --> 00:06:36,968
ANY DESIRE TO SERVE
IN IT?

112
00:06:37,033 --> 00:06:39,634
NOPE, DAD. GUESS I'VE
SEEN TOO MANY NEWSREELS.

113
00:06:39,701 --> 00:06:41,868
DO YOU KNOW WHAT THE SOUND
OF THOSE ANCHOR CHAINS

114
00:06:41,934 --> 00:06:44,767
RATTLING DOWN A FEW
MINUTES AGO MEANT TO ME?

115
00:06:44,834 --> 00:06:47,567
IT MEANS THE END
OF MY LAST SEA DUTY.

116
00:06:47,634 --> 00:06:49,767
TOMORROW MORNING, I'M TO
BE RELIEVED OF COMMAND.

117
00:06:49,834 --> 00:06:52,000
YOU STILL HAVE 4 MORE
YEARS BEFORE YOU'RE RETIRED.

118
00:06:52,067 --> 00:06:54,033
YOU'RE GOING TO BE SUPERINTENDENT
OF THE NAVAL ACADEMY.

119
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:55,267
YES.

120
00:06:55,334 --> 00:06:57,067
SEEMS LIKE A GREAT HONOR-
GOING BACK TO THE ACADEMY

121
00:06:57,133 --> 00:06:59,434
AND BEING HEAD OF THE SAME SCHOOL
THAT YOU ENTERED AS A PLEBE.

122
00:06:59,501 --> 00:07:01,167
IT'S GOING TO BE
A VERY EMPTY HONOR

123
00:07:01,234 --> 00:07:02,467
UNLESS YOU CHANGE
YOUR MIND.

124
00:07:02,534 --> 00:07:04,501
IT WOULD BE A GREAT
HONOR... IF I COULD KNOW

125
00:07:04,567 --> 00:07:06,400
THAT YOU WERE GOING TO WALK THROUGH
THOSE GATES TO BECOME A MIDSHIPMAN

126
00:07:06,467 --> 00:07:08,400
THE SAME AS I DID AND
MY FATHER BEFORE ME...

127
00:07:08,467 --> 00:07:09,767
THAT YOU'D BE
THE NEXT MELVILLE

128
00:07:09,834 --> 00:07:11,734
TO WRITE A NEW CHAPTER
IN NAVAL RECORDS.

129
00:07:11,801 --> 00:07:14,467
OH, I KNOW, BUT THAT'S JUST
WHY I DON'T WANT IT, DAD.

130
00:07:14,534 --> 00:07:16,501
I DON'T WANT TO BE
JUST ANOTHER MELVILLE.

131
00:07:16,567 --> 00:07:20,100
IF I WOUND UP ANYTHING SHORT OF BEING
AN ADMIRAL, I'D BE A BLACK SHEEP.

132
00:07:20,167 --> 00:07:22,400
YOU KNOW, SON, I THINK I
COULD UNDERSTAND YOU BETTER

133
00:07:22,467 --> 00:07:25,801
IF YOU'D CHOSEN TO BE, SAY,
AN ENGINEER OR A DOCTOR...

134
00:07:25,868 --> 00:07:28,133
SOMETHING TO SUSTAIN
THE IDEA OF SERVICE.

135
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:30,400
OH, WELL, I...
I'M SERVICING.

136
00:07:30,467 --> 00:07:33,067
IT'S A LITTLE BIT DIFFERENT.
PEOPLE GOT TO BE ENTERTAINED.

137
00:07:33,133 --> 00:07:36,300
YOU KNOW THAT I ALREADY MAKE 3
TIMES AS MUCH MONEY AS YOU DO A YEAR?

138
00:07:36,367 --> 00:07:38,334
THAT'S NOT BAD
FOR A YOUNGSTER.

139
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:42,000
TOOK YOU 40 YEARS TO GET TO
THE TOP OF YOUR PROFESSION, DAD.

140
00:07:42,067 --> 00:07:43,267
IT'S ONLY TAKEN ME
TWO YEARS.

141
00:07:43,334 --> 00:07:47,834
MY FOREBEARS HAVE ALWAYS
SERVED COUNTRY AND FLAG...

142
00:07:47,901 --> 00:07:48,834
NOT DOLLARS.

143
00:07:48,901 --> 00:07:51,734
OH, DAD. YOU'RE
A SENTIMENTALIST.

144
00:07:51,801 --> 00:07:54,234
TODAY, EVERYTHING BOILS
DOWN TO DOLLARS AND CENTS,

145
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:55,934
NOT THE STAR-SPANGLED
BANNER.

146
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:56,968
I SEE.

147
00:07:57,033 --> 00:07:58,801
OH, I DON'T MEAN THAT
REALLY, THOUGH.

148
00:07:58,868 --> 00:08:01,868
I MEAN THAT I'VE JUST HEARD
"NAVY, NAVY, NAVY, NAVY"

149
00:08:01,934 --> 00:08:04,501
EVER SINCE I'VE BEEN OLD ENOUGH
TO UNDERSTAND WHAT IT MEANT.

150
00:08:04,567 --> 00:08:06,367
I WANT TO STAND
ON MY OWN.

151
00:08:07,534 --> 00:08:09,234
I'VE GOT A DIFFERENT
KIND OF A JOB.

152
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:11,601
THERE IS SOMETHING I
WOULD LIKE YOU TO DO, SON,

153
00:08:11,667 --> 00:08:13,801
IF IT ISN'T
TOO MUCH NAVY.

154
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:15,200
I'D LIKE YOU TO BE
ABOARD TOMORROW MORNING

155
00:08:15,267 --> 00:08:17,234
WHEN I SAY GOOD-BYE
TO MY LAST SEA DUTY...

156
00:08:17,300 --> 00:08:19,200
WHEN I TURN OVER
MY LAST COMMAND.

157
00:08:19,267 --> 00:08:21,267
SURE, DAD. I'VE GOT A COUPLE
FRIENDS WHO'D LIKE TO SEE THE SHOW.

158
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:22,534
CAN I BRING THEM
ON BOARD?

159
00:08:22,601 --> 00:08:25,334
WELL, THIS ISN'T EXACTLY
GOING TO BE A SHOW, DICK.

160
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:27,400
I'D, UH, PREFER
THAT YOU CAME ALONE.

161
00:08:27,467 --> 00:08:29,300
OK, DAD.
WHAT TIME WILL IT BE?

162
00:08:29,367 --> 00:08:30,334
4 BELLS.

163
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:31,634
4 BELLS?
4 BELLS IN THE NAVY...

164
00:08:31,701 --> 00:08:33,901
THAT'S, UH, 10:00 IN
THE MORNING TO ME, HUH?

165
00:08:33,968 --> 00:08:34,901
YES, YES.

166
00:08:34,968 --> 00:08:35,901
OK, DAD.

167
00:08:35,968 --> 00:08:37,367
I'LL BE HERE.
GOOD-BYE.

168
00:08:45,067 --> 00:08:47,767
Melville, on radio: GOOD EVENING,
EVERYBODY. THIS IS DICK MELVILLE SPEAKING.

169
00:08:47,834 --> 00:08:50,100
TONIGHT IS "WELCOME NAVY NIGHT"
HERE AT THE SKY CLUB.

170
00:08:50,167 --> 00:08:53,334
I'VE WRITTEN A NEW SONG THAT
I WANT TO DEDICATE TO THE NAVY

171
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:56,567
AND TO ADMIRAL RICHARD MELVILLE,
THE BOSS OF THE FLEET-

172
00:08:56,634 --> 00:08:57,901
<i>DON'T GIVE UP THE SHIP.</i>

173
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:10,334
* SHIPMATES, STAND TOGETHER

174
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:14,334
* DON'T GIVE UP THE SHIP

175
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:18,467
* FAIR OR STORMY WEATHER

176
00:09:18,534 --> 00:09:22,901
* WE WON'T GIVE UP,
WE WON'T GIVE UP THE SHIP *

177
00:09:22,968 --> 00:09:26,901
* FRIENDS AND PALS FOREVER

178
00:09:26,968 --> 00:09:31,067
* IT'S A LONG, LONG TRIP

179
00:09:31,133 --> 00:09:33,200
* IF YOU HAVE TO
TAKE A LICKIN' *

180
00:09:33,267 --> 00:09:35,667
* CARRY ON AND QUIT
YOUR KICKIN' *

181
00:09:35,734 --> 00:09:39,868
* DON'T GIVE UP THE SHIP

182
00:09:42,367 --> 00:09:43,667
TABLE FOR TWO, PLEASE.

183
00:09:43,734 --> 00:09:46,601
SORRY, SIR. EVERY TABLE IS
TAKEN. HAVE YOU RESERVATIONS?

184
00:09:46,667 --> 00:09:48,667
NO, WE HAVEN'T, AND I'M
GLAD EVERY TABLE IS TAKEN,

185
00:09:48,734 --> 00:09:51,501
AND I HOPE YOU HAVE A VERY
PLEASANT EVENING. COME ON, JUNE.

186
00:09:51,567 --> 00:09:53,067
BUT MR. MELVILLE
WAS EXPECTING US.

187
00:09:53,133 --> 00:09:54,634
OH, ARE YOU MISS BLACKBURN AND ESCORT?

188
00:09:54,701 --> 00:09:55,701
YES.

189
00:09:55,767 --> 00:09:58,400
ACCEPT MY APOLOGIES.
THIS WAY, PLEASE.

190
00:10:01,934 --> 00:10:05,701
* SHIPMATES, STAND TOGETHER

191
00:10:05,767 --> 00:10:07,501
* DON'T GIVE UP...

192
00:10:07,567 --> 00:10:10,400
"MISS BLACKBURN AND EXCESS
BAGGAGE," HE SHOULD HAVE SAID.

193
00:10:10,467 --> 00:10:13,667
<i>WHY DIDN'T DICK LEAVE
THE TABLE IN MY NAME?</i>

194
00:10:13,734 --> 00:10:15,901
MAYBE HE LIKES ME
BETTER THAN YOU.

195
00:10:15,968 --> 00:10:17,767
WELL, I HOPE SO.

196
00:10:17,834 --> 00:10:22,701
* FRIENDS AND PALS FOREVER

197
00:10:22,767 --> 00:10:26,334
* IT'S A LONG, LONG TRIP

198
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:28,100
* IF YOU HAVE TO
TAKE A LICKIN' *

199
00:10:28,167 --> 00:10:30,601
* CARRY ON
AND QUIT YOUR KICKIN' *

200
00:10:30,667 --> 00:10:34,367
* DON'T GIVE UP THE SHIP

201
00:10:38,267 --> 00:10:40,634
HE OUGHT TO BE MARCHING
BEHIND THAT DITTY

202
00:10:40,701 --> 00:10:42,534
INSTEAD OF YELPING IT
OVER A MICROPHONE.

203
00:10:42,601 --> 00:10:44,834
SHH!

204
00:10:46,434 --> 00:10:48,167
GOOD EVENING,
MISS BLACKBURN.

205
00:10:48,234 --> 00:10:50,167
AND A SOUR EVENING TO YOU, MR. STERLING.

206
00:10:50,234 --> 00:10:52,634
<i>AFTER HEARING YOU SING,
IT REALLY IS SOUR.</i>

207
00:10:52,701 --> 00:10:53,601
MAY I?

208
00:10:53,667 --> 00:10:55,400
NOT IF YOU'RE
A MIND READER.

209
00:10:55,467 --> 00:10:57,234
DEPENDS ON WHOSE
MIND HE'S READING.

210
00:10:57,300 --> 00:10:58,834
THANK YOU. NO SOONER SAID THAN SAT.

211
00:10:58,901 --> 00:11:01,567
YOU KNOW, I DON'T HAVE TO SING
ANOTHER SONG FOR ABOUT 10 MINUTES.

212
00:11:01,634 --> 00:11:03,300
I WISH IT WERE
10 YEARS.

213
00:11:03,367 --> 00:11:05,133
OH, YOU'RE A PIKER.
WHAT'S 10 YEARS?

214
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:07,667
HAVE YOU EVER HEARD OF THE
ASTRONOMICAL TERM "LIGHT YEARS"?

215
00:11:07,734 --> 00:11:09,267
MILLIONS OF YEARS,
BILLIONS OF YEARS?

216
00:11:09,334 --> 00:11:10,734
WHY, DO YOU KNOW
THAT-

217
00:11:10,801 --> 00:11:13,801
WHY, DO YOU KNOW I'M NOT THE
LEAST BIT INTERESTED IN ASTRONOMY?

218
00:11:13,868 --> 00:11:14,834
ARE YOU?

219
00:11:14,901 --> 00:11:16,133
OH, INTENSELY.

220
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:18,501
THEN I SHALL TAKE THIS RARE
OPPORTUNITY AND SHOW YOU

221
00:11:18,567 --> 00:11:21,267
AN ASTRONOMICAL PHENOMENA WHICH
YOU REALLY CAN'T AFFORD TO MISS.

222
00:11:21,334 --> 00:11:22,901
WILL YOU EXCUSE US, PLEASE? NO.

223
00:11:22,968 --> 00:11:26,200
OH, THAT'S VERY SWEET
OF YOU, TED. THANKS.

224
00:11:33,033 --> 00:11:35,234
AND NOW FOR THAT RARE
ASTRONOMICAL PHENOMENA

225
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:37,000
WHICH YOU CAN'T
AFFORD TO MISS...

226
00:11:37,067 --> 00:11:39,033
OR MYSELF, EITHER,
FOR THAT MATTER.

227
00:11:39,100 --> 00:11:42,100
LET'S, UH...
LET ME SEE.

228
00:11:42,167 --> 00:11:44,868
LET'S CONSIDER THE STAR "R," PLANET "Q."

229
00:11:44,934 --> 00:11:49,167
IT, UH-I THINK YOU CAN
SEE BETTER FROM OVER HERE.

230
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:52,801
WE CAN SPECIFY
ITS POSITION

231
00:11:52,868 --> 00:11:56,300
BY GIVING ITS ZENITH DISTANCE, ZQ...

232
00:11:57,801 --> 00:12:02,033
AND THE AZIMUTH FROM THE SOUTH POINT
- THAT'S ANGLE QZS.

233
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:05,667
OR BY GIVING THE NORTH
POLE A DISTANCE-PQ-

234
00:12:05,734 --> 00:12:08,734
AND THE ANGLE QPZ,

235
00:12:08,801 --> 00:12:13,300
WHICH, OF COURSE YOU KNOW,
IS CALLED THE "R" ANGLE.

236
00:12:13,367 --> 00:12:15,400
YOU KNOW MORE ABOUT ASTRONOMY THAN I DO.

237
00:12:15,467 --> 00:12:17,100
MAYBE.

238
00:12:17,167 --> 00:12:20,000
THEN WHY DID YOU COME OUT HERE WITH ME?

239
00:12:20,067 --> 00:12:23,167
BECAUSE YOU
WANTED ME TO.

240
00:12:31,334 --> 00:12:33,167
I WISH I KNEW SOMETHING
ABOUT THE LAWS OF GRAVITY.

241
00:12:33,234 --> 00:12:34,701
WHY?

242
00:12:34,767 --> 00:12:36,334
THEN I'D KNOW WHY
I'VE FALLEN FOR YOU

243
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:38,501
FASTER THAN
A TON OF BRICKS.

244
00:12:38,567 --> 00:12:39,734
CAN I SEE YOU
TOMORROW...

245
00:12:39,801 --> 00:12:41,234
AND EVERY TOMORROW
FROM THEN ON?

246
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:44,100
YOU'D HAVE TO FALL ALL THE
WAY TO ANNAPOLIS TO DO THAT.

247
00:12:44,167 --> 00:12:46,367
OH, WHY MUST YOU GO
BACK TO ANNAPOLIS?

248
00:12:46,434 --> 00:12:48,434
I LIVE THERE
AND I WORK THERE,

249
00:12:48,501 --> 00:12:50,567
TEACHING 8-YEAR-OLD
NAVY JUNIORS

250
00:12:50,634 --> 00:12:52,968
HOW TO PUT THEIR HEELS
IN FRONT OF THEIR TOES.

251
00:12:53,033 --> 00:12:57,434
AH, NEW YORK CAN'T KEEP ME
HERE, WITH YOU DOWN IN CRAB TOWN.

252
00:12:57,501 --> 00:13:00,467
YOU MEANT WHAT YOU SAID
ABOUT NOT MARRYING NAVY?

253
00:13:00,534 --> 00:13:02,200
UH-HUH.

254
00:13:02,267 --> 00:13:05,467
THEN, BY THE GRACE OF THE
STARS AND LAWS OF GRAVITY,

255
00:13:05,534 --> 00:13:08,634
I'M GOING TO MAKE YOU
WANT TO MARRY ME.

256
00:13:08,701 --> 00:13:11,467
<i>I WISH I KNEW SOMETHING
ABOUT THE LAWS OF GRAVITY.</i>

257
00:13:11,534 --> 00:13:13,000
WHY?

258
00:13:13,067 --> 00:13:16,534
THEN I'D KNOW WHY I'VE
FALLEN FOR YOU FASTER...

259
00:13:24,067 --> 00:13:26,300
OH, MY.
GOOD OLD ZENITH.

260
00:13:26,367 --> 00:13:29,400
HA HA! OH, POOR OLD TED'S
ALONE. COME ON.

261
00:13:29,467 --> 00:13:30,767
ALL RIGHT.

262
00:13:39,067 --> 00:13:41,033
SORRY, TED.

263
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:45,534
I'VE BEEN WORKING ON A DREAM
PORTRAIT OF YOU, MR. MELVILLE.

264
00:13:45,601 --> 00:13:48,267
Melville: WELL... IT
HARDLY DOES ME JUSTICE.

265
00:13:48,334 --> 00:13:49,701
Ted: OH, I THINK SO.

266
00:13:49,767 --> 00:13:51,400
A LITTLE MORE PRACTICE,
YOU OUGHT TO BE ABLE

267
00:13:51,467 --> 00:13:52,801
TO DRAW FOR
THE FUNNY PAPERS.

268
00:13:52,868 --> 00:13:55,567
I'VE GOT TO GO TO WORK,
DARLING. SEE YOU LATER.

269
00:13:56,934 --> 00:13:58,834
THAT'S VERY PRETTY,
TED. WHAT IS IT?

270
00:13:58,901 --> 00:14:00,734
WHY, IT'S A...

271
00:14:03,667 --> 00:14:06,901
* WHEN SOMEONE TELLS
ME TO MARCH *

272
00:14:06,968 --> 00:14:08,801
* OR TO HALT

273
00:14:08,868 --> 00:14:11,100
* MY SOUL REBELS

274
00:14:11,167 --> 00:14:14,467
* I'M THAT WAY
TO A FAULT *

275
00:14:14,534 --> 00:14:18,234
* NO RULES OR REGULATIONS

276
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:20,300
* WOULD I OBEY

277
00:14:20,367 --> 00:14:26,033
* THEN I MET YOU,
AND I KNEW RIGHT AWAY *

278
00:14:27,367 --> 00:14:30,300
* IF YOU'RE THE CAPTAIN

279
00:14:30,367 --> 00:14:32,367
* I'LL BE THE CREW

280
00:14:32,434 --> 00:14:37,834
* 'CAUSE I'D JUST LOVE
TO TAKE ORDERS FROM YOU *

281
00:14:39,067 --> 00:14:41,000
* YOU BLOW THE BUGLE

282
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:44,067
* AND I'LL JUMP THROUGH

283
00:14:44,133 --> 00:14:46,667
* OH, HOW I'D LOVE TO

284
00:14:46,734 --> 00:14:49,734
* TAKE ORDERS FROM YOU

285
00:14:49,801 --> 00:14:52,367
* I KNOW THAT RULES
WERE MEANT FOR FOOLS *

286
00:14:52,434 --> 00:14:54,667
* THAT'S ONE THING
I HAVE LEARNED *

287
00:14:54,734 --> 00:14:58,033
* BUT I'M GOING IN
FOR DISCIPLINE *

288
00:14:58,100 --> 00:15:02,634
* WHEREVER YOU'RE CONCERNED

289
00:15:02,701 --> 00:15:05,834
* IF YOU SAY, "KISS ME,"

290
00:15:05,901 --> 00:15:07,834
* THAT'S WHAT I'LL DO

291
00:15:07,901 --> 00:15:09,868
* 'CAUSE I'D JUST LOVE TO

292
00:15:09,934 --> 00:15:13,234
* TAKE ORDERS FROM YOU

293
00:15:22,033 --> 00:15:24,267
CONVERSE!

294
00:15:24,334 --> 00:15:25,300
YES, SIR.

295
00:15:25,367 --> 00:15:26,868
WHAT TIME IS IT?
10 OF 10:00, SIR.

296
00:15:26,934 --> 00:15:28,767
10 OF 10:00. I'VE ONLY GOT 10
MINUTES TO GET TO THE FLAGSHIP.

297
00:15:28,834 --> 00:15:31,067
GET MY CLOTHES DOWN TO THE CAR. CALL
THE DRIVER. TELL HIM TO HURRY UP.

298
00:15:31,133 --> 00:15:32,400
WHAT CLOTHES, SIR?

299
00:15:32,467 --> 00:15:34,100
ANYTHING! ANYTHING! I HAVEN'T
GOT TIME TO DRESS HERE.

300
00:15:34,167 --> 00:15:35,100
VERY GOOD, SIR.

301
00:15:35,167 --> 00:15:36,767
TELL HIM TO MEET US
DOWN IN FRONT.

302
00:15:38,667 --> 00:15:40,667
COME ON! COME ON!

303
00:15:40,734 --> 00:15:42,000
OK, ORIN!

304
00:15:44,267 --> 00:15:47,634
MY DAD WILL NEVER
GET OVER THIS.

305
00:15:47,701 --> 00:15:50,868
WHEW! WHY DIDN'T I
GET TO BED EARLIER?

306
00:15:51,868 --> 00:15:54,067
STEP ON IT,
WILL YOU, ORIN?!

307
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,801
AM I TOO LATE
FOR THE CEREMONY?

308
00:16:02,868 --> 00:16:04,367
NO. THE ADMIRAL
IS STILL BELOW.

309
00:16:04,434 --> 00:16:05,901
THANK YOU, SIR.

310
00:16:09,501 --> 00:16:11,701
HELLO, DAD.
I'M LATE.

311
00:16:11,767 --> 00:16:13,601
SO I SEE.

312
00:16:16,167 --> 00:16:17,100
HELLO, DICK.

313
00:16:17,167 --> 00:16:18,968
HOW ARE YOU, SIR?

314
00:16:24,801 --> 00:16:28,133
TO THE OFFICERS AND MEN
OF THE UNITED STATES FLEET,

315
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:30,267
AND TO THE PERSONNEL OF
THIS SHIP IN PARTICULAR,

316
00:16:30,334 --> 00:16:35,167
IT IS WITH GREAT REGRET
THAT I TURN OVER MY COMMAND.

317
00:16:35,234 --> 00:16:38,400
BEFORE DOING SO, I WANT
TO EXPRESS MY APPRECIATION

318
00:16:38,467 --> 00:16:43,067
FOR THE COOPERATION AND LOYALTY
THAT I HAVE RECEIVED FROM ALL HANDS

319
00:16:43,133 --> 00:16:45,734
DURING THE LONG PERIOD
OF MY COMMAND.

320
00:16:45,801 --> 00:16:48,634
AND IT IS A MATTER OF
GENUINE SATISFACTION TO ME

321
00:16:48,701 --> 00:16:52,634
THAT MY SUCCESSOR,
YOUR FUTURE COMMANDER IN CHIEF,

322
00:16:52,701 --> 00:16:55,834
IS MY LIFELONG FRIEND
AND CLASSMATE,

323
00:16:55,901 --> 00:16:57,067
ADMIRAL GRAVES.

324
00:16:57,133 --> 00:16:58,367
AND MY PARTING WORD

325
00:16:58,434 --> 00:17:06,167
TO ALL HANDS IS, "KEEP
THIS FLEET FIT TO FIGHT."

326
00:17:06,234 --> 00:17:09,534
I WILL NOW READ
MY ORDERS.

327
00:17:09,601 --> 00:17:11,267
"NAVY DEPARTMENT,
WASHINGTON.

328
00:17:11,334 --> 00:17:13,834
"FROM SECRETARY OF THE NAVY
TO ADMIRAL RICHARD MELVILLE,

329
00:17:13,901 --> 00:17:15,567
"COMMANDER IN CHIEF,
UNITED STATES FLEET.

330
00:17:15,634 --> 00:17:17,067
CHANGE OF DUTY.

331
00:17:17,133 --> 00:17:19,234
"BEEN RELIEVED OF DUTY
ON OR ABOUT 29th OF MAY.

332
00:17:19,300 --> 00:17:21,033
"YOU WILL REGARD YOURSELF
AS DETACHED FROM DUTY

333
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:22,734
"AS COMMANDER IN CHIEF
OF THE UNITED STATES FLEET

334
00:17:22,801 --> 00:17:25,167
"AND PROCEED TO ANNAPOLIS, MARYLAND,
WHERE YOU WILL REPORT FOR DUTY

335
00:17:25,234 --> 00:17:27,834
"AS SUPERINTENDENT OF THE
UNITED STATES NAVAL ACADEMY.

336
00:17:27,901 --> 00:17:31,067
"THIS IS A PERMANENT SHORE DUTY,
REQUIRED FOR THE PUBLIC'S INTEREST.

337
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:33,901
SIGNED,
SECRETARY OF THE NAVY."

338
00:17:37,634 --> 00:17:41,067
CAPTAIN, HAUL DOWN
MY FLAG, SIR.

339
00:17:41,133 --> 00:17:42,901
AYE, AYE.

340
00:18:00,167 --> 00:18:02,601
OH, HELLO, SON.

341
00:18:02,667 --> 00:18:05,434
YOU'LL HAVE TO EXCUSE ME A MINUTE
WHILE I GET INTO CIVILIAN CLOTHES.

342
00:18:05,501 --> 00:18:06,968
I'M FLYING TO WASHINGTON.

343
00:18:07,033 --> 00:18:08,834
OK, DAD.

344
00:18:12,934 --> 00:18:14,400
THANK YOU, DICK.
YOU'LL BE STANDING

345
00:18:14,467 --> 00:18:16,467
IN YOUR FATHER'S SHOES UP THERE SOMEDAY.

346
00:18:16,534 --> 00:18:17,734
AND AFTER 40 YEARS
OF SERVICE,

347
00:18:17,801 --> 00:18:20,434
ALL I'D HAVE TO SHOW
FOR IT IS ONE OF THESE?

348
00:18:20,501 --> 00:18:21,667
NO, I'M AFRAID NOT.

349
00:18:21,734 --> 00:18:24,100
NO, FRED. DICK'S NOT GOING
TO TRY FOR THE ACADEMY.

350
00:18:24,167 --> 00:18:25,934
HE'S EVIDENTLY FOUND OUT
THERE'S A LITTLE SOMETHING

351
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:28,501
MORE TO IT THAN JUST GOING DOWN
THERE AND KNOCKING AT THE GATE.

352
00:18:28,567 --> 00:18:30,234
IT'S STILL A PRETTY
TOUGH PLACE TO GET INTO.

353
00:18:30,300 --> 00:18:35,133
HE REALIZES THAT BEING A MELVILLE
DOESN'T MAKE A BIT OF DIFFERENCE.

354
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:38,501
LOOKS TO ME LIKE
A CASE OF COLD FEET.

355
00:18:38,567 --> 00:18:42,434
HE KNOWS HE COULDN'T EVEN
PASS THE ENTRANCE EXAMINATION.

356
00:18:46,968 --> 00:18:52,267
WHY, DICK, I DIDN'T THINK YOU
WOULD SHY AT THOSE EXAMINATIONS.

357
00:18:52,334 --> 00:18:54,367
ALWAYS UNDERSTOOD
YOU WERE PRETTY SAVVY

358
00:18:54,434 --> 00:18:57,067
IN YOUR STUDIES
AT COLLEGE.

359
00:18:57,133 --> 00:18:58,834
EXCUSE ME, SIR.

360
00:19:02,634 --> 00:19:04,868
WHAT DO YOU THINK
I AM, DAD? A NINCOMPOOP?

361
00:19:04,934 --> 00:19:06,534
HA HA! WHAT DO
YOU MEAN, SON?

362
00:19:06,601 --> 00:19:09,501
TELLING ADMIRAL GRAVES I HAD COLD FEET
AND COULDN'T PASS THOSE EXAMINATIONS.

363
00:19:09,567 --> 00:19:11,133
WELL, THAT'S
THE TRUTH, ISN'T IT?

364
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:12,234
OH, I SEE.

365
00:19:12,300 --> 00:19:13,767
YOU THINK ALL THOSE
MIDSHIPMEN DOWN THERE

366
00:19:13,834 --> 00:19:15,300
ARE SMARTER THAN
YOUR OWN SON.

367
00:19:15,367 --> 00:19:17,267
SINCE YOU WANT TO PUT IT
THAT WAY...

368
00:19:17,334 --> 00:19:20,033
THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT I THINK.

369
00:19:20,100 --> 00:19:22,601
I'VE GIVEN THIS THING A
LOT OF CONSIDERATION, DICK,

370
00:19:22,667 --> 00:19:25,834
AND MAYBE YOU'RE RIGHT IN
THIS SINGING CAREER OF YOURS,

371
00:19:25,901 --> 00:19:28,000
SINCE YOU COULDN'T BEAR
THE DISGRACE OF FAILING

372
00:19:28,067 --> 00:19:29,701
IN THE ENTRANCE
EXAMINATION.

373
00:19:29,767 --> 00:19:32,200
DISGRACE? FAILURE?

374
00:19:32,267 --> 00:19:35,033
I COULD PASS THOSE
EXAMINATIONS WITH MY EYES SHUT.

375
00:19:35,100 --> 00:19:36,067
YOU THINK SO?

376
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:37,067
I KNOW SO.

377
00:19:37,133 --> 00:19:39,267
HA HA HA!
I DOUBT THAT.

378
00:19:39,334 --> 00:19:42,033
I'LL SHOW YOU THAT
YOUR SON IS NO NITWIT.

379
00:19:42,100 --> 00:19:43,601
I'LL PROVE TO YOU
THAT I'M SMART ENOUGH

380
00:19:43,667 --> 00:19:46,567
TO GET INTO THE NAVY
IF I WANT TO.

381
00:19:46,634 --> 00:19:50,501
I'LL PASS THOSE EXAMINATIONS, BUT I
DON'T HAVE TO ACCEPT THE APPOINTMENT.

382
00:19:55,534 --> 00:19:57,501
WELL, FRED...

383
00:19:57,567 --> 00:19:59,501
A WORLD OF LUCK
TO YOU.

384
00:19:59,567 --> 00:20:00,701
THANK YOU, DICK.

385
00:20:00,767 --> 00:20:02,734
GOOD-BYE.

386
00:20:31,767 --> 00:20:34,868
TIME'S UP, BOYS.
TURN YOUR PAPERS IN.

387
00:20:34,934 --> 00:20:38,334
PRINCIPALS AND ALTERNATES WILL RECEIVE
WORD OF APPOINTMENT OR FAILURE BY MAIL

388
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,834
FROM THE NAVY
DEPARTMENT.

389
00:20:39,901 --> 00:20:41,100
GOOD LUCK.

390
00:20:59,667 --> 00:21:02,300
TRY THIS ON YOUR
RADIO, SPARKS.

391
00:21:09,167 --> 00:21:10,968
I'VE PASSED!

392
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:14,400
Sparks: HA HA!

393
00:21:14,467 --> 00:21:15,767
HEY, SPARKS!
YOU GOT CHINA!

394
00:21:15,834 --> 00:21:17,834
YOU CAN KEEP CHINA!
YOU CAN KEEP THE RADIO!

395
00:21:17,901 --> 00:21:21,834
I'M GOING TO
THE NAVAL ACADEMY! HEY!

396
00:21:21,901 --> 00:21:24,200
HEY! LOOK HERE, Y'ALL!
I GOT IT! HEY, LOOK!

397
00:21:24,267 --> 00:21:25,434
WHAT HAVE YOU GOT?

398
00:21:25,501 --> 00:21:26,968
MY APPOINTMENT! I'M
GOING TO THE NAVAL ACADEMY

399
00:21:27,033 --> 00:21:28,968
TO LEARN HOW TO GIVE
YOU MUGS ORDERS!

400
00:21:29,033 --> 00:21:30,300
<i>HEY,
WE'LL TAKE ORDERS!</i>

401
00:21:30,367 --> 00:21:32,334
All: YEAH!

402
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:34,634
ALL I COULD READ WAS
"NAVY DEPARTMENT."

403
00:21:36,167 --> 00:21:38,167
WHAT DOES IT SAY, SON?

404
00:21:39,100 --> 00:21:41,567
IT JUST SAYS
I PASSED, MA.

405
00:21:42,667 --> 00:21:45,634
HA HA. I PASSED!

406
00:21:48,534 --> 00:21:50,334
DICK, HERE'S THAT LETTER
YOU WERE TALKING ABOUT

407
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:51,367
FROM THE NAVY
DEPARTMENT.

408
00:21:51,434 --> 00:21:52,868
YOUR CHAUFFEUR
JUST BROUGHT IT OVER.

409
00:21:52,934 --> 00:21:54,167
THANKS, HARRY.

410
00:21:55,434 --> 00:21:56,767
WELL, I PASSED-

411
00:21:56,834 --> 00:21:58,667
PASSED MY EXAMINATIONS
FOR THE NAVAL ACADEMY.

412
00:21:58,734 --> 00:22:01,601
HA HA HA! WHAT A JOKE THIS
IS GOING TO BE ON YOUR FATHER

413
00:22:01,667 --> 00:22:04,033
WHEN HE FINDS OUT YOU'RE
GOING TO TURN IT DOWN.

414
00:22:04,100 --> 00:22:06,367
OH, BUT THE JOKE'S
ON ME, HARRY.

415
00:22:06,434 --> 00:22:08,267
I CAN'T TURN THE OLD
ADMIRAL DOWN.

416
00:22:08,334 --> 00:22:09,534
YOU MEAN,
YOU'RE GOING TO...

417
00:22:09,601 --> 00:22:11,167
THAT'S WHAT I MEAN.

418
00:22:15,133 --> 00:22:16,701
Melville, on radio:
GOOD EVENING, EVERYBODY.

419
00:22:16,767 --> 00:22:18,801
THIS IS DICK MELVILLE SPEAKING
TO YOU FROM THE SKY CLUB

420
00:22:18,868 --> 00:22:20,067
IN GOOD OLD NEW YORK CITY.

421
00:22:20,133 --> 00:22:23,434
TOM, TURN OFF
THAT RADIO.

422
00:22:28,901 --> 00:22:30,167
TOM!

423
00:22:36,167 --> 00:22:38,701
Melville: THIS IS
GOOD-BYE TO RADIO, FOR ME,

424
00:22:38,767 --> 00:22:41,601
BECAUSE I'VE PASSED MY ENTRANCE
EXAMINATION TO ANNAPOLIS,

425
00:22:41,667 --> 00:22:44,534
AND I'M GOING NAVY!

426
00:22:44,601 --> 00:22:46,767
Tom: DID YOU CALL,
ADMIRAL, SIR?

427
00:22:46,834 --> 00:22:50,033
YES! YES, TOM, YOU POUR ME
A GLASS OF THAT OLDEST PORT.

428
00:22:50,100 --> 00:22:53,000
Melville:
*... THE SHIP

429
00:22:53,067 --> 00:22:56,200
* FAIR OR STORMY WEATHER

430
00:22:56,267 --> 00:23:00,801
* WE WON'T GIVE UP,
WE WON'T GIVE UP THE SHIP *

431
00:23:00,868 --> 00:23:05,133
* FRIENDS AND PALS FOREVER

432
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:08,701
* IT'S A LONG, LONG TRIP

433
00:23:08,767 --> 00:23:10,701
* IF YOU HAVE
TO TAKE A LICKIN' *

434
00:23:10,767 --> 00:23:13,033
* CARRY ON AND
QUIT YOUR KICKIN' *

435
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:17,100
* DON'T GIVE UP THE SHIP

436
00:23:52,801 --> 00:23:53,767
NO SMOKING, SIR.

437
00:23:53,834 --> 00:23:56,334
OH, I'M SORRY.
I FORGOT.

438
00:23:57,267 --> 00:23:58,267
THANK YOU.

439
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,701
WHOA, YOU DUDE!

440
00:24:28,767 --> 00:24:30,667
ARE YOU ENTERING HERE?

441
00:24:30,734 --> 00:24:32,801
WELL, WHAT DOES
IT LOOK LIKE?

442
00:24:32,868 --> 00:24:35,367
FROM WHAT I HEAR TELL OF
THE ACADEMY, MY FRIEND,

443
00:24:35,434 --> 00:24:37,501
YOU'RE GOING TO LIVE
TO REGRET THAT ENTRANCE.

444
00:24:37,567 --> 00:24:40,234
DID YOU PAY THOSE GUYS TO DO THAT?

445
00:24:41,567 --> 00:24:42,934
YOU BOYS KNOW
WHERE YOU'RE GOING?

446
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:44,200
NO, SIR.
NO, SIR.

447
00:24:44,267 --> 00:24:46,701
ALL RIGHT, FOLLOW ME. I'LL SHOW YOU.

448
00:25:06,601 --> 00:25:07,601
SAY, "AH."

449
00:25:07,667 --> 00:25:17,567
AHHH.

450
00:25:19,501 --> 00:25:21,667
HEE HEE.

451
00:25:21,734 --> 00:25:22,968
WHOA!

452
00:25:24,701 --> 00:25:27,100
MERCY, DOC!

453
00:25:27,167 --> 00:25:29,033
Doctor:
TURN YOUR HEAD.

454
00:25:29,100 --> 00:25:31,200
NOW COUGH.

455
00:25:31,267 --> 00:25:33,167
THE OTHER SIDE.

456
00:25:33,901 --> 00:25:35,601
COUGH AGAIN.

457
00:25:47,834 --> 00:25:49,400
WHOA!

458
00:25:51,033 --> 00:25:53,501
DID YOU EVER THINK OF
TOTING THEM UP ONE AT A TIME?

459
00:25:53,567 --> 00:25:54,501
CAN YOU DO THAT?

460
00:25:54,567 --> 00:25:55,934
SURE. WHY NOT?
I'M DOING IT.

461
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,801
NOTHING IN THE REGULATIONS AGAINST IT.

462
00:25:57,868 --> 00:25:58,901
THAT'S FUNNY.

463
00:25:58,968 --> 00:26:01,033
IT THOUGHT IT WAS A GAME OR SOMETHING...

464
00:26:01,100 --> 00:26:02,601
TESTING
THE MANHOOD IN YOU.

465
00:26:02,667 --> 00:26:05,367
OH, NO.
THAT COMES LATER.

466
00:26:15,133 --> 00:26:16,234
WELL, ROOMMATES,

467
00:26:16,300 --> 00:26:18,067
IN CASE YOU DIDN'T CATCH
IT, THE NAME'S BROWN.

468
00:26:18,133 --> 00:26:19,501
THEY CHRISTENED ME
LAFAYETTE,

469
00:26:19,567 --> 00:26:21,801
ON ACCOUNT OF THAT'S WHAT PERSHING
SAID THE MORNING I ARRIVED.

470
00:26:21,868 --> 00:26:24,434
YOU KNOW, "LAFAYETTE,
HERE WE ARE."

471
00:26:24,501 --> 00:26:28,033
ONLY IT WAS ME, SPARKS, IN
ARKANSAS, AND PERSHING WAS IN FRANCE.

472
00:26:28,100 --> 00:26:30,501
I CAME IN FROM
THE FLEET, FELLAS-

473
00:26:30,567 --> 00:26:32,133
<i>JOHNNY LAWRENCE,
FROM THE TEXAS.</i>

474
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:33,501
UH, THEY CALL ME
COXSWAIN.

475
00:26:33,567 --> 00:26:36,701
MY NAME'S LINCOLN-
ARIZONA.

476
00:26:36,767 --> 00:26:38,634
CALL ME COWBOY.

477
00:26:38,701 --> 00:26:39,968
DICK MELVILLE,
NEW YORK.

478
00:26:40,033 --> 00:26:41,501
Sparks: BOY, YOU DON'T
NEED TO TELL US WHO YOU ARE.

479
00:26:41,567 --> 00:26:43,200
WE GOT A LOAD OF YOU
WHEN YOU WALKED IN.

480
00:26:43,267 --> 00:26:45,367
Cowboy: I'LL SAY.

481
00:26:45,434 --> 00:26:47,000
EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT,
FELLAS?

482
00:26:47,067 --> 00:26:49,067
HAVE YOU GOT
A LITTLE ICE WATER?

483
00:26:49,133 --> 00:26:52,133
I- HA HA HA.

484
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:54,534
YOUR PLEBE SUMMER WILL
BE A BREEZE, MISTERS,

485
00:26:54,601 --> 00:26:57,467
COMPARED TO WHAT YOU'LL GET WHEN THE
FIRST CLASS COMES BACK FROM THE CRUISE.

486
00:26:57,534 --> 00:26:59,267
WE CAN TAKE IT,
SIR.

487
00:27:00,267 --> 00:27:01,767
WE'LL SEE.

488
00:27:01,834 --> 00:27:02,868
IN THE MEANTIME,
BEAR A HAND.

489
00:27:02,934 --> 00:27:04,767
GET YOUR MARKING DONE,
YOUR LOCKERS STOWED.

490
00:27:04,834 --> 00:27:07,367
WHEN ASSEMBLY SOUNDS, FALL
IN BELOW TO BE SWORN IN.

491
00:27:07,434 --> 00:27:10,567
I'LL MEET YOU THERE.
AND DON'T FORGET...

492
00:27:10,634 --> 00:27:13,434
THE FIRST CLASS CRUISE
GETS BACK IN SEPTEMBER.

493
00:27:13,501 --> 00:27:16,501
AND THAT GOES FOR YOU,
MR. MELVILLE.

494
00:27:19,501 --> 00:27:21,200
HE JUST SAID THAT
TO SCARE YOU.

495
00:27:21,267 --> 00:27:22,834
WHAT DOES HE MEAN,
"GET YOUR MARKING DONE"?

496
00:27:22,901 --> 00:27:25,968
GET OUT YOUR INDELIBLE INK AND
YOU MARK AN OUTFIT. I'LL SHOW YOU.

497
00:27:29,567 --> 00:27:30,467
ASSEMBLY! LET'S GO!

498
00:27:30,534 --> 00:27:31,634
Melville:
LIKE WE ARE?

499
00:27:31,701 --> 00:27:32,834
BOYS, WHEN THAT
BUGLE BLOWS,

500
00:27:32,901 --> 00:27:34,300
YOU GO
HOWEVER YOU ARE!

501
00:27:36,467 --> 00:27:40,167
Man: RAISE YOUR RIGHT HANDS,
GENTLEMEN, AND REPEAT AFTER ME.

502
00:27:40,234 --> 00:27:43,901
I, HAVING BEEN APPOINTED A MIDSHIPMAN
IN THE UNITED STATES NAVY...

503
00:27:43,968 --> 00:27:47,868
All: I, HAVING BEEN APPOINTED A
MIDSHIPMAN IN THE UNITED STATES NAVY...

504
00:27:47,934 --> 00:27:50,701
DO SOLEMNLY SWEAR...

505
00:27:50,767 --> 00:27:54,167
THAT I WILL SUPPORT AND DEFEND THE
CONSTITUTION OF THE UNITED STATES...

506
00:27:54,234 --> 00:27:57,701
THAT I WILL SUPPORT AND DEFEND THE
CONSTITUTION OF THE UNITED STATES...

507
00:27:57,767 --> 00:28:03,200
AGAINST ALL ENEMIES,
FOREIGN AND DOMESTIC...

508
00:28:03,267 --> 00:28:05,701
AND I WILL BEAR TRUE FAITH
AND ALLEGIANCE TO THE SAME.

509
00:28:05,767 --> 00:28:08,767
AND I WILL BEAR TRUE FAITH
AND ALLEGIANCE TO THE SAME.

510
00:28:08,834 --> 00:28:10,868
AND I TAKE THIS OBLIGATION FREELY...

511
00:28:10,934 --> 00:28:13,167
AND I TAKE THIS OBLIGATION FREELY...

512
00:28:13,234 --> 00:28:16,033
WITHOUT ANY METTLE RESERVATION
OR PURPOSE OF EVASION...

513
00:28:16,100 --> 00:28:19,501
WITHOUT ANY METTLE RESERVATION
OR PURPOSE OF EVASION...

514
00:28:19,567 --> 00:28:21,567
THAT I WILL WELL AND
FAITHFULLY DISCHARGE THE DUTIES

515
00:28:21,634 --> 00:28:23,734
OF THE OFFICE ON WHICH
I AM ABOUT TO ENTER...

516
00:28:23,801 --> 00:28:26,534
THAT I WILL WELL AND
FAITHFULLY DISCHARGE THE DUTIES

517
00:28:26,601 --> 00:28:28,634
OF THE OFFICE UPON WHICH
I AM ABOUT TO ENTER...

518
00:28:28,701 --> 00:28:31,434
SO HELP ME, GOD.

519
00:28:31,501 --> 00:28:32,968
HANDS DOWN, GENTLEMEN.

520
00:28:33,033 --> 00:28:36,467
YOU'RE NOW MIDSHIPMEN IN THE
UNITED STATES NAVY. CONGRATULATIONS.

521
00:28:36,534 --> 00:28:37,968
FOR THE BENEFIT
OF MY ROOMMATES,

522
00:28:38,033 --> 00:28:40,667
I WILL NOW READ FROM THE REGULATIONS
OF THE U.S. NAVAL ACADEMY'S

523
00:28:40,734 --> 00:28:42,067
<i>THE STOWAGE OF LOCKERS.</i>

524
00:28:42,133 --> 00:28:43,234
DO YOU FOLLOW ME?

525
00:28:43,300 --> 00:28:45,234
ONE FOR EACH OCCUPANT.

526
00:28:45,300 --> 00:28:46,734
"4 INCHES FROM WALL
OR CASINGS.

527
00:28:46,801 --> 00:28:48,133
"CONTENTS NEATLY ARRANGED
AS FOLLOWS:

528
00:28:48,200 --> 00:28:50,834
TOWELS, SHEETS, PILLOW CASES,

529
00:28:50,901 --> 00:28:52,968
"SPREADS, CLOTHES, BAGS,
AND SPLASHES, SO ARRANGED

530
00:28:53,033 --> 00:28:54,801
"THAT SMOOTH FOLDS,
AND NOT ROUGH EDGES, SHOW.

531
00:28:54,868 --> 00:28:56,100
BOTTLES,

532
00:28:56,167 --> 00:28:58,300
"WRITING MATERIALS, LETTERS,
PAPERS, BRUSHES, SOAP BOXES,

533
00:28:58,367 --> 00:28:59,734
SMALL ARTICLES,
SEWING KIT."

534
00:28:59,801 --> 00:29:01,234
SEWING KIT?

535
00:29:01,300 --> 00:29:03,734
YOU MEAN, WE HAVE TO DO OUR
OWN SEWING IN THIS PLACE?

536
00:29:05,534 --> 00:29:07,701
Coxswain: I DON'T KNOW WHAT
ELSE YOU DO WITH A SEWING KIT

537
00:29:07,767 --> 00:29:08,834
BESIDES SEW WITH IT.

538
00:29:08,901 --> 00:29:10,667
I'LL DO ALL YOUR DARNING
FOR A DIME A SOCK.

539
00:29:10,734 --> 00:29:13,467
I WAS THE BEST LITTLE
DARNER ON MY BATTLESHIP.

540
00:29:13,534 --> 00:29:14,901
I DON'T KNOW
HOW THEY EXPECT US

541
00:29:14,968 --> 00:29:16,167
TO GET ALL THIS JUNK
IN HERE, ANYWAY.

542
00:29:16,234 --> 00:29:17,934
JUST LISTEN
TO PAPA, CROONER.

543
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:19,300
HE'S READING YOU
HOW TO DO IT.

544
00:29:19,367 --> 00:29:22,634
HEY, YOU-YOU. DON'T CALL
ME CROONER. GET ME?

545
00:29:22,701 --> 00:29:26,000
OK. OK. OK.

546
00:29:27,701 --> 00:29:29,133
CAN I HELP YOU
WITH YOUR LOCKER, DICK?

547
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:30,701
MINE IS ALMOST DONE.

548
00:29:30,767 --> 00:29:32,868
NO, THANKS, COXSWAIN.
I CAN STOW MY OWN.

549
00:29:32,934 --> 00:29:34,701
Cowboy: I COULD USE
A LITTLE HELP, COXSWAIN.

550
00:29:34,767 --> 00:29:37,067
ALL RIGHT.

551
00:29:37,133 --> 00:29:41,033
SAY! ARE YOU REALLY THAT
SINGING FELLA FROM NEW YORK CITY?

552
00:29:43,133 --> 00:29:45,901
I THOUGHT SO.

553
00:29:45,968 --> 00:29:48,567
I NEVER CARED MUCH
FOR YOUR SINGING MYSELF,

554
00:29:48,634 --> 00:29:53,200
BUT I ALWAYS SAYS, "EVERY
FELLA TO HIS OWN OPINION."

555
00:29:53,267 --> 00:29:55,701
I'M NOT ASKING ANYBODY
FOR ANY OPINIONS.

556
00:29:55,767 --> 00:29:57,868
I CAME HERE AS A MIDSHIPMAN,
NOT AS A CROONER.

557
00:29:57,934 --> 00:30:00,801
THE SOONER YOU FORGET YOU EVER HEARD ME
ON THE RADIO, THE BETTER I'LL LIKE IT.

558
00:30:00,868 --> 00:30:03,734
YOU OUGHT TO TELL THAT
TO THOSE UPPERCLASSMEN.

559
00:30:03,801 --> 00:30:05,701
THEY SEEN YOU
WHEN YOU DONE IT,

560
00:30:05,767 --> 00:30:08,767
IF I MIGHT LAPSE INTO
THE COLLOQUIAL.

561
00:30:08,834 --> 00:30:11,033
YOU KNOW, IT'S GONNA
TAKE YOU A LONG TIME

562
00:30:11,100 --> 00:30:13,167
TO LIVE DOWN THAT
ENTRANCE OF YOURS.

563
00:30:15,133 --> 00:30:16,968
WASN'T A RADIO ISSUED
TO ANY OF YOU GUYS?

564
00:30:17,033 --> 00:30:19,100
I DIDN'T SEE ANY
RADIO ON MY LIST.

565
00:30:19,167 --> 00:30:20,734
I DON'T THINK PLEBES
RATE RADIOS.

566
00:30:20,801 --> 00:30:24,367
I WAS RAISED ON A RADIO.
GOT TO HAVE A RADIO.

567
00:30:29,133 --> 00:30:31,367
HOW'S ABOUT A RADIO
FOR 3305?

568
00:30:31,434 --> 00:30:33,901
WE DON'T SALUTE WHEN
WE'RE UNCOVERED, MISTER.

569
00:30:37,934 --> 00:30:39,567
HAVE YOU STOWED
YOUR LOCKER YET?

570
00:30:39,634 --> 00:30:41,033
OH, YES, YES, YES.

571
00:30:41,100 --> 00:30:42,067
WHOSE STUFF
IS THAT?

572
00:30:42,133 --> 00:30:43,934
MINE, SIR. YOU SEE,
IT DIDN'T QUITE FIT.

573
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:45,901
BETTER START OVER AGAIN AND MAKE IT FIT.

574
00:30:45,968 --> 00:30:47,367
THERE ARE
YOUR RULES.

575
00:30:47,434 --> 00:30:48,567
YES, SIR.

576
00:30:49,534 --> 00:30:50,901
HOW'S ABOUT
A RADIO?

577
00:30:50,968 --> 00:30:55,133
YOU'LL HAVE TO WAIT TWO YEARS
TO RATE A RADIO IN YOUR ROOM.

578
00:30:55,200 --> 00:30:57,067
A MAN THAT'S BEEN
RAISED ON RADIOS

579
00:30:57,133 --> 00:30:58,400
CAN'T LIVE
WITHOUT A RADIO.

580
00:30:58,467 --> 00:31:00,701
AND SINCE I'M A MAN WHO
KNOWS SOMETHING ABOUT A RADIO,

581
00:31:00,767 --> 00:31:02,100
I'M GOING TO HAVE
A RADIO,

582
00:31:02,167 --> 00:31:04,234
EVEN IF THE GREAT DICK MELVILLE
ISN'T ON WEDNESDAY NIGHTS.

583
00:31:04,300 --> 00:31:05,834
AND TO BE SURE,
I WAS ALWAYS ONE

584
00:31:05,901 --> 00:31:07,167
TO LISTEN IN
ON WEDNESDAY NIGHTS.

585
00:31:07,234 --> 00:31:08,734
I STILL GOT TO HAVE
A RADIO,

586
00:31:08,801 --> 00:31:11,801
EVEN IF MR. MELVILLE IS IN
ANNAPOLIS AND NOT STATION WBNY,

587
00:31:11,868 --> 00:31:14,634
AND FURTHERMORE, I'M
GOING TO HAVE A RADIO!

588
00:31:17,634 --> 00:31:19,567
SQUEEZE HARD.

589
00:31:19,634 --> 00:31:20,567
200.

590
00:31:21,934 --> 00:31:24,234
225.

591
00:31:28,167 --> 00:31:29,400
180.

592
00:31:29,467 --> 00:31:31,133
OK.

593
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:39,734
PULL. PULL HARD.

594
00:31:39,801 --> 00:31:41,167
60.

595
00:31:42,300 --> 00:31:43,934
NEXT.

596
00:31:51,334 --> 00:31:53,267
SQUARE YOUR HATS!

597
00:31:55,534 --> 00:31:57,567
SQUAD, ATTENTION!

598
00:31:58,901 --> 00:32:01,267
RIGHT FACE!

599
00:32:01,334 --> 00:32:03,601
LEFT FACE!

600
00:32:03,667 --> 00:32:06,634
MR. LINCOLN, HOLD YOUR
HAT IN YOUR RIGHT HAND.

601
00:32:06,701 --> 00:32:08,667
YOU SURE THAT'S
YOUR RIGHT HAND?

602
00:32:08,734 --> 00:32:09,701
YES, SIR.

603
00:32:09,767 --> 00:32:10,968
REMEMBER IT.

604
00:32:13,234 --> 00:32:14,601
HOW YOU FEELING?

605
00:32:14,667 --> 00:32:16,033
OK, PAL.

606
00:32:41,868 --> 00:32:44,100
GOOD MORNING, SIR.

607
00:32:44,167 --> 00:32:45,501
MORNING.

608
00:32:58,334 --> 00:33:00,033
WHO'S IN CHARGE?

609
00:33:00,100 --> 00:33:01,033
I AM, SIR.

610
00:33:01,100 --> 00:33:02,767
MIDSHIPMAN MELVILLE,
FOURTH CLASS.

611
00:33:02,834 --> 00:33:05,801
PLACE HIM ON THE REPORT.
DUST BEHIND THE RADIATOR.

612
00:33:08,434 --> 00:33:10,767
SORRY, DICK. NEXT TIME,
ONE OF US WILL BE IN CHARGE.

613
00:33:10,834 --> 00:33:13,234
I'D LIKE TO KNOW WHAT BEARING
DUST HAS ON MY BECOMING AN OFFICER.

614
00:33:13,300 --> 00:33:14,667
YOU THINK WE'D LOSE
A NAVAL BATTLE

615
00:33:14,734 --> 00:33:16,934
JUST BECAUSE WE LEFT A SQUARE
INCH OF DUST BEHIND A RADIATOR?

616
00:33:17,000 --> 00:33:18,567
I WASN'T GONNA
SAY ANYTHING,

617
00:33:18,634 --> 00:33:20,200
BUT INASMUCH
AS I HEAR,

618
00:33:20,267 --> 00:33:23,033
YOUR FATHER WAS THE ADMIRAL
OF THE FLEET AWHILE BACK.

619
00:33:23,100 --> 00:33:25,400
SEEMS TO ME LIKE
AN ADMIRAL'S SON

620
00:33:25,467 --> 00:33:26,767
WOULD KNOW MORE
ABOUT THOSE THINGS

621
00:33:26,834 --> 00:33:30,167
THAN A MERE GUY FROM ARIZONA
WHO WAS WEANED ON DUST

622
00:33:30,234 --> 00:33:32,434
AND JUST DON'T LIKE IT
BY INSTINCT.

623
00:33:34,234 --> 00:33:35,834
MIDSHIPMAN MELVILLE?

624
00:33:35,901 --> 00:33:36,901
YES, SIR.

625
00:33:36,968 --> 00:33:38,234
REPORT TODAY TO
THE SUPERINTENDENT.

626
00:33:38,300 --> 00:33:39,400
AYE, AYE, SIR.

627
00:33:39,467 --> 00:33:40,734
CARRY ON.

628
00:33:43,167 --> 00:33:44,667
YOU SENT FOR ME, SIR?

629
00:33:44,734 --> 00:33:46,734
WELL, HELLO, DICK.

630
00:33:46,801 --> 00:33:47,801
HELLO, DAD.

631
00:33:47,868 --> 00:33:50,200
I HAD HOPED YOU'D
CALL ON ME AT THE HOUSE.

632
00:33:50,267 --> 00:33:52,400
I DIDN'T WANT ANYONE TO FEEL
THAT I WAS TAKING ADVANTAGE

633
00:33:52,467 --> 00:33:53,400
OF OUR RELATIONSHIP,
SIR.

634
00:33:53,467 --> 00:33:54,701
THAT'S COMMENDABLE,

635
00:33:54,767 --> 00:33:57,267
BUT I DON'T THINK ANYONE
IS GOING TO CRITICIZE A SON

636
00:33:57,334 --> 00:34:00,100
FOR CALLING ON
HIS OWN FATHER.

637
00:34:00,167 --> 00:34:02,634
YOUR WHITES DON'T
SEEM TO FIT YOU YET,

638
00:34:02,701 --> 00:34:05,567
BUT THEY'LL SOON SHRINK
DOWN TO YOUR SIZE.

639
00:34:05,634 --> 00:34:09,234
I HAVEN'T HAD A CHANCE TO
CONGRATULATE YOU BEFORE, MY SON.

640
00:34:09,300 --> 00:34:11,167
I'M PROUD OF YOU.

641
00:34:12,467 --> 00:34:14,801
TELL ME, HOW DO YOU
LIKE THE ACADEMY?

642
00:34:14,868 --> 00:34:19,334
I THINK I MADE A FOOL OUT OF
MYSELF BY COMING HERE, SIR.

643
00:34:20,968 --> 00:34:25,234
MIDSHIPMAN MELVILLE, YOU HAVE A
GREAT MANY LESSONS TO LEARN HERE,

644
00:34:25,300 --> 00:34:27,667
AND A FEW IDEAS OF YOUR
OWN YOU'D BETTER FORGET.

645
00:34:27,734 --> 00:34:30,133
I SUGGEST YOU REPORT
BACK TO YOUR QUARTERS

646
00:34:30,200 --> 00:34:32,267
AND THINK THEM OVER.

647
00:34:33,467 --> 00:34:35,501
AYE, AYE, SIR.

648
00:34:52,968 --> 00:34:54,667
EXCUSE ME, PLEASE.

649
00:34:56,734 --> 00:34:58,300
HELLO, MISTER.

650
00:34:58,367 --> 00:35:01,534
HAVE YOU A TWIN BROTHER
IN NEW YORK WHO SINGS

651
00:35:01,601 --> 00:35:03,968
AND DOESN'T BELIEVE
IN THE NAVY?

652
00:35:04,033 --> 00:35:06,300
NO, I HAVEN'T
A TWIN BROTHER.

653
00:35:06,367 --> 00:35:08,300
I'M THE SAME DUCK YOU
TALKED TO IN NEW YORK,

654
00:35:08,367 --> 00:35:09,734
ONLY I SUDDENLY WENT
SOFT IN THE HEAD.

655
00:35:09,801 --> 00:35:10,901
WHAT HAPPENED, DICK?

656
00:35:10,968 --> 00:35:11,934
I DON'T KNOW.

657
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:14,200
<i>BANDS PLAYING
STARS AND STRIPES,</i>

658
00:35:14,267 --> 00:35:16,167
PEOPLE SCREAMING
AND HOLLERING,

659
00:35:16,234 --> 00:35:17,834
DAD GOING OVER THE
SIDE, BLOOD WILL TELL,

660
00:35:17,901 --> 00:35:18,901
I DON'T KNOW.

661
00:35:18,968 --> 00:35:21,400
I JUST WENT OFF MY NUT AND HERE I AM.

662
00:35:21,467 --> 00:35:22,901
FURTHERMORE, I WISH
I HAD A TWIN BROTHER

663
00:35:22,968 --> 00:35:26,300
SO HE COULD TRADE
PLACES WITH ME RIGHT NOW.

664
00:35:26,367 --> 00:35:28,934
I HAVE TO BE AT BANCROFT
IN TIME FOR FORMATION.

665
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:30,000
DICK...

666
00:35:30,067 --> 00:35:33,367
FORGET WHAT I SAID
ABOUT NAVY IN NEW YORK.

667
00:35:33,434 --> 00:35:35,400
I'D LIKE YOU TO COME
SEE ME.

668
00:35:35,467 --> 00:35:38,267
I'D LIKE TO
SEE YOU, TOO.

669
00:35:38,334 --> 00:35:40,300
ONLY UNFORTUNATELY,

670
00:35:40,367 --> 00:35:42,234
THEY HAVE A BOOK OF
REGULATIONS AROUND HERE,

671
00:35:42,300 --> 00:35:43,767
AND PLEBES AREN'T
ALLOWED OUT OF THESE WALLS

672
00:35:43,834 --> 00:35:45,100
EXCEPT ON LABOR DAY

673
00:35:45,167 --> 00:35:47,567
AND WHAT IS LAUGHINGLY
CALLED INDEPENDENCE DAY.

674
00:35:51,701 --> 00:35:54,968
GOOD-BYE.

675
00:36:05,801 --> 00:36:07,601
HEY, WAKE UP,
FELLAS!

676
00:36:07,667 --> 00:36:10,534
THE CREWS IS IN!
THE CREWS IS IN!

677
00:36:22,667 --> 00:36:23,634
THERE THEY BE.

678
00:36:23,701 --> 00:36:25,567
LOADED TO THE GUNNEL
WITH FIRST CLASSMEN.

679
00:36:25,634 --> 00:36:28,267
NOW WE GET IT! NOW THE
REIGN OF TERROR STARTS!

680
00:36:28,334 --> 00:36:29,667
REIGN OF TERROR?

681
00:36:29,734 --> 00:36:33,534
I SUPPOSE YOU THINK THIS PAST
SUMMER'S BEEN A SWEET DREAM.

682
00:36:43,667 --> 00:36:45,901
PULL OUT
YOUR CHEST.

683
00:36:45,968 --> 00:36:47,667
DROP YOUR
SHOULDERS.

684
00:36:50,234 --> 00:36:51,400
WHAT'S THAT?

685
00:36:51,467 --> 00:36:52,801
TH-THAT'S ME, SIR.

686
00:36:52,868 --> 00:36:55,067
WELL,
PULL IT IN.

687
00:36:55,133 --> 00:36:57,100
PULL YOUR HANDS
BACK.

688
00:37:00,133 --> 00:37:02,167
SQUARE THAT CAP,
MR. MELVILLE.

689
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:06,200
A LITTLE MORE.

690
00:37:08,801 --> 00:37:11,467
MR. LAWRENCE, DID YOU
BRUSH OFF THIS MORNING?

691
00:37:11,534 --> 00:37:12,734
YES, SIR.

692
00:37:12,801 --> 00:37:14,200
WITH A BLANKET OR
WITH A BATH TOWEL?

693
00:37:14,267 --> 00:37:16,601
WITH A BL-UH, WITH
A CLOTHES BRUSH, SIR.

694
00:37:16,667 --> 00:37:18,334
YOU SURE YOU HAVE
A CLOTHES BRUSH?

695
00:37:18,400 --> 00:37:19,667
YES, SIR.

696
00:37:19,734 --> 00:37:21,067
DO YOU USE IT?

697
00:37:21,133 --> 00:37:22,567
UH, YES, SIR.

698
00:37:22,634 --> 00:37:25,400
DON'T COME DOWN HERE TO
FORMATION AGAIN LOOKING LIKE THIS.

699
00:37:25,467 --> 00:37:26,434
NO, SIR.

700
00:37:26,501 --> 00:37:27,434
"AYE, AYE, SIR."

701
00:37:27,501 --> 00:37:29,000
AYE, AYE, SIR.

702
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:32,534
REGIMENT, ATTENTION!

703
00:37:32,601 --> 00:37:35,567
ATTENTION!

704
00:37:35,634 --> 00:37:37,901
TURN SQUADS RIGHT
AND LEFT!

705
00:37:37,968 --> 00:37:38,934
TURN SQUAD
RIGHT!

706
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:40,934
SQUAD RIGHT!

707
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:42,834
MARCH!

708
00:38:21,534 --> 00:38:27,934
HUP! HUP! HUP! HUP!
HUP! HUP! HUP!

709
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:30,200
SEAT!

710
00:38:39,834 --> 00:38:41,467
WHAT'S YOUR NAME, MISTER,
AND WHERE ARE YOU FROM?

711
00:38:41,534 --> 00:38:43,167
MIDSHIPMAN MELVILLE.
NEW YORK, SIR.

712
00:38:43,234 --> 00:38:44,601
WHAT DO THE GIRLS
CALL YOU, MISTER?

713
00:38:44,667 --> 00:38:45,567
DICK, SIR.

714
00:38:45,634 --> 00:38:46,601
WHY, MISTER?

715
00:38:46,667 --> 00:38:47,667
THAT'S MY NAME, SIR.

716
00:38:47,734 --> 00:38:49,934
ARE YOU DICK MELVILLE,
THE RADIO SONGBIRD?

717
00:38:50,767 --> 00:38:52,200
ARE YOU?
YES, SIR.

718
00:38:52,267 --> 00:38:55,567
THOUGHT SO. WE'VE HEARD ABOUT
YOU AND YOUR MUSICAL INTRODUCTION

719
00:38:55,634 --> 00:38:56,667
TO THE ACADEMY.

720
00:38:56,734 --> 00:38:59,033
WE'LL DO OUR BEST TO
GET MIDSHIPMAN INTO YOU

721
00:38:59,100 --> 00:39:00,000
AND CROONER OUT OF YOU.

722
00:39:00,067 --> 00:39:01,000
THANK YOU, SIR.

723
00:39:01,067 --> 00:39:03,367
THE PAIN AND PLEASURE
WILL BE OURS.

724
00:39:03,434 --> 00:39:05,767
WHO ARE YOU, MISTER,
AND WHERE ARE YOU FROM?

725
00:39:05,834 --> 00:39:07,601
WHO, ME, SIR?

726
00:39:07,667 --> 00:39:08,634
YES.

727
00:39:08,701 --> 00:39:10,300
MIDSHIPMAN LAWRENCE.
EX-BLUEJACKETS, SIR.

728
00:39:10,367 --> 00:39:11,701
HOW ARE YOU WITH
THE DRAGS, MISTER?

729
00:39:11,767 --> 00:39:13,801
I BEG YOUR PARDON,
SIR?

730
00:39:13,868 --> 00:39:15,601
THE DRAGS, THE FEMMES,
THE LADIES.

731
00:39:15,667 --> 00:39:17,734
HOW DO YOU GET
ALONG WITH THEM?

732
00:39:17,801 --> 00:39:18,968
OH, VERY WELL.

733
00:39:19,033 --> 00:39:20,567
VERY WELL
INDEED, SIR.

734
00:39:20,634 --> 00:39:22,234
WHAT DO THE GIRLS
CALL YOU, MISTER?

735
00:39:22,300 --> 00:39:24,067
THEY DON'T HAVE TO
CALL ME, SIR.

736
00:39:24,133 --> 00:39:26,334
WHEREVER THEY ARE, I'M
GENERALLY JOHNNY-ON-THE-SPOT.

737
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:28,501
SUBMERGE.

738
00:39:36,334 --> 00:39:37,834
WHAT'S YOUR NAME AND
WHERE ARE YOU FROM, MISTER?

739
00:39:37,901 --> 00:39:39,968
MIDSHIPMAN BROWN, SIR.
ARKANSAS.

740
00:39:41,801 --> 00:39:43,767
STARBOARD RUNNING LIGHT,
MASTHEAD LIGHT,

741
00:39:43,834 --> 00:39:44,868
BRIGHT LIGHT, SIR.

742
00:39:44,934 --> 00:39:46,868
LIGHT BUOY WATCH ALERT.

743
00:39:46,934 --> 00:39:48,701
WIPE IT OFF.

744
00:39:54,467 --> 00:39:59,801
TOOT, TOOT,
TOOT, TOOT!

745
00:40:03,534 --> 00:40:04,467
I REQUEST PERMISSION

746
00:40:04,534 --> 00:40:07,167
TO COME ABOARD, SIR.

747
00:40:07,234 --> 00:40:09,934
COME ABOARD AND EAT
A SQUARE MEAL.

748
00:40:29,534 --> 00:40:31,501
WIPE IT OFF.

749
00:40:32,734 --> 00:40:34,501
IN THE FUTURE,
MR. MELVILLE,

750
00:40:34,567 --> 00:40:37,667
DON'T TURN ON THAT PERSONALITY
SMILE FOR OUR BENEFIT.

751
00:40:37,734 --> 00:40:41,133
WE'RE YOUR PUBLIC NOW,
AND WE DON'T LIKE IT.

752
00:40:41,200 --> 00:40:43,601
AYE, AYE, SIR.

753
00:40:45,834 --> 00:40:48,434
WHY DON'T THEY GROW UP AND
FORGET THAT CHILD'S PLAY?

754
00:40:48,501 --> 00:40:50,367
MR. MELVILLE!

755
00:40:50,434 --> 00:40:51,367
YES, SIR.

756
00:40:51,434 --> 00:40:53,601
COME HERE.

757
00:40:55,701 --> 00:40:58,000
WHEN ARE YOU GOING TO GET
THE WORD, MR. SONGBIRD?

758
00:40:58,067 --> 00:40:59,767
PLEBES AREN'T ALLOWED
TO TALK IN THE CORRIDORS.

759
00:40:59,834 --> 00:41:00,734
WHO'S SPONSORING YOU?

760
00:41:00,801 --> 00:41:02,133
NOBODY, SIR.

761
00:41:02,200 --> 00:41:04,868
YOU MEAN TO TELL ME THAT YOU
HAVEN'T GOT A FIRST CLASSMAN?

762
00:41:04,934 --> 00:41:06,067
NO, SIR.

763
00:41:06,133 --> 00:41:07,667
THEN YOU'RE ASSIGNED
TO ME,

764
00:41:07,734 --> 00:41:09,400
PAINFUL THOUGH
THE DUTY WILL BE.

765
00:41:09,467 --> 00:41:12,067
COME TO REPORT BEFORE
EAST FORMATION AFTER DINNER

766
00:41:12,133 --> 00:41:14,133
AND AFTER RELEASE
FROM STUDY HOUR.

767
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:16,133
WHAT FOR, SIR?

768
00:41:16,200 --> 00:41:18,601
I'VE ALWAYS BEEN A GREAT
ADMIRER OF THE WORKS

769
00:41:18,667 --> 00:41:22,934
OF ABDUL ABULBUL AMIR,
AND SO HAVE MY ROOMMATES.

770
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:26,300
WE FEEL THAT THE SOONER YOU GET
THE CROONER OUT OF YOUR TONSILS

771
00:41:26,367 --> 00:41:28,133
AND MIDSHIPMAN INTO
YOUR HEAD, THE BETTER.

772
00:41:28,200 --> 00:41:30,267
FOLLOW ME.

773
00:41:32,234 --> 00:41:34,767
I GAVE THIS NIGHTINGALE
AN ORDER, GENTLEMEN,

774
00:41:34,834 --> 00:41:36,667
AND HE ASKED, "WHAT FOR?"

775
00:41:36,734 --> 00:41:39,901
AND I'VE SUGGESTED A LITTLE
MUSICALECTOMY FOR THE ANSWER.

776
00:41:39,968 --> 00:41:41,400
FINE IDEA.

777
00:41:41,467 --> 00:41:44,534
<i>WE ONLY HAVE TIME FOR THE
FIRST 100 VERSES OF ABDUL</i>

778
00:41:44,601 --> 00:41:46,067
THIS AFTERNOON.

779
00:41:48,634 --> 00:41:49,634
BEAUTIFUL,
BEAUTIFUL,

780
00:41:49,701 --> 00:41:50,968
<i>BUT WE PREFER
ABDUL.</i>

781
00:41:51,033 --> 00:41:53,400
<i>ABDUL ABULBUL AMIR,
FIRST VERSE.</i>

782
00:41:53,467 --> 00:41:55,868
* OH

783
00:41:55,934 --> 00:41:59,701
* THE SONS OF THE PROPHET
ARE BRAVE MEN AND BOLD *

784
00:41:59,767 --> 00:42:03,467
* AND QUITE UNACCUSTOMED
TO FEAR *

785
00:42:03,534 --> 00:42:07,901
* BUT BRAVEST BY FAR
IN THE RANKS OF THE SHAH *

786
00:42:07,968 --> 00:42:11,534
* WAS ABDUL ABULBUL AMIR

787
00:42:11,601 --> 00:42:12,667
SECOND VERSE.

788
00:42:12,734 --> 00:42:14,667
* OH

789
00:42:14,734 --> 00:42:17,901
* IF YOU WANTED A MAN
TO ENCOURAGE THE VAN *

790
00:42:17,968 --> 00:42:21,534
* OR HARASS THE FOE
FROM THE REAR *

791
00:42:21,601 --> 00:42:25,400
* TO STORM FORT OR REDOUBT,
YOU HAD ONLY TO SHOUT *

792
00:42:25,467 --> 00:42:29,167
* FOR ABDUL ABULBUL AMIR

793
00:42:29,234 --> 00:42:30,434
THIRD VERSE.

794
00:42:30,501 --> 00:42:31,567
* OH...

795
00:42:31,634 --> 00:42:34,701
NICE. NICE, PEAR-SHAPED TONES.

796
00:42:34,767 --> 00:42:37,234
* OH

797
00:42:37,300 --> 00:42:40,200
* THE HEROES WERE PLENTY
AND WELL-KNOWN TO FAME *

798
00:42:40,267 --> 00:42:45,133
* IN THE RANKS THAT WERE
LED BY THE TSAR *

799
00:42:45,200 --> 00:42:49,534
* BUT BRAVEST BY FAR WAS
A MAN BY THE NAME *

800
00:42:49,601 --> 00:42:54,767
* OF IVAN SKAVINSKY SKAVAR

801
00:42:54,834 --> 00:42:56,200
FOURTH VERSE.

802
00:42:56,267 --> 00:42:57,734
I THINK THE ACOUSTICS ARE MUCH BETTER

803
00:42:57,801 --> 00:42:58,968
OVER HERE
IN THE SHOWER.

804
00:43:00,033 --> 00:43:01,801
AYE, AYE, SIR.

805
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:05,133
FOURTH VERSE.

806
00:43:05,200 --> 00:43:09,167
* OH

807
00:43:09,234 --> 00:43:11,133
YOU'RE QUITE
RIGHT, SIR.

808
00:43:11,200 --> 00:43:13,100
* OH

809
00:43:13,167 --> 00:43:18,100
* HE COULD JUMP 50 YARDS,
TELL FORTUNES AT CARDS *

810
00:43:18,167 --> 00:43:23,000
* STRUM ON THE SPANISH
GUITAR... *

811
00:43:23,067 --> 00:43:24,734
HUNDREDTH VERSE.

812
00:43:24,801 --> 00:43:28,567
* OH

813
00:43:28,634 --> 00:43:34,434
* THIS MUSCOVITE MAIDEN
A LONG VIGIL KEEPS *

814
00:43:34,501 --> 00:43:40,100
* EACH NIGHT 'NEATH
THE COLD WINTRY STAR *

815
00:43:40,167 --> 00:43:45,467
* AND THE NAME THAT SHE MURMURS
IN VAIN AS SHE WEEPS *

816
00:43:45,534 --> 00:43:53,567
* WAS IVAN SKAVINSKY SKAVAR

817
00:44:11,501 --> 00:44:13,133
OH, MR. MELVILLE?

818
00:44:14,167 --> 00:44:15,767
YES, SIR.

819
00:44:15,834 --> 00:44:18,434
<i>I'M A LITTLE MIXED UP ON THE
38th VERSE OF ABDUL ABULBUL AMIR.</i>

820
00:44:18,501 --> 00:44:20,267
WILL YOU SING IT
FOR ME, PLEASE?

821
00:44:20,334 --> 00:44:21,701
RIGHT HERE, SIR?

822
00:44:21,767 --> 00:44:24,200
RIGHT HERE AND WITH
GESTURES, PLEASE.

823
00:44:24,267 --> 00:44:25,267
* OH

824
00:44:25,334 --> 00:44:27,267
* ONE DAY,
THIS BOLD RUSSIAN *

825
00:44:27,334 --> 00:44:30,901
* HE SHOULDERED
HIS GUN *

826
00:44:30,968 --> 00:44:35,033
* AND DONNED HIS MOST
TRUCULENT SNEER *

827
00:44:37,000 --> 00:44:38,901
* DOWNTOWN HE DID GO

828
00:44:38,968 --> 00:44:41,501
* WHERE HE TROD
ON THE TOE *

829
00:44:41,567 --> 00:44:44,467
* OF
ABDUL ABULBUL AMIR *

830
00:44:44,534 --> 00:44:45,934
THANK YOU VERY MUCH,
MISTER,

831
00:44:46,000 --> 00:44:48,167
AND A HAPPY ABDUL
ABULBUL TO YOU.

832
00:44:48,234 --> 00:44:51,400
AND A HAPPY ABDUL
ABULBUL TO YOU, SIR.

833
00:45:47,601 --> 00:45:49,634
DISMISS THE BATTALION!

834
00:45:49,701 --> 00:45:51,400
THIRD BATTALION
DISMISSED.

835
00:45:55,801 --> 00:45:57,300
WELL, HERE I AM.

836
00:45:57,367 --> 00:45:59,067
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"HERE I AM"?

837
00:45:59,133 --> 00:46:00,334
<i>SORRY, FELLAS,
HERE I AM.</i>

838
00:46:00,400 --> 00:46:02,367
COME ALONG, JUNE.

839
00:46:03,734 --> 00:46:05,901
THE MORE I STAY
INSIDE THESE WALLS,

840
00:46:05,968 --> 00:46:07,267
THE MORE I FEEL
LIKE A CONVICT.

841
00:46:07,334 --> 00:46:09,033
ALL PLEBES
GO THROUGH THAT.

842
00:46:09,100 --> 00:46:11,801
IT'S THE WAY YOU EARN YOUR
LIBERTIES FOR NEXT YEAR.

843
00:46:11,868 --> 00:46:13,934
I DON'T WANT
ANY NEXT YEAR.

844
00:46:14,000 --> 00:46:15,200
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

845
00:46:15,267 --> 00:46:17,834
I'M JUST FED UP ON BEING
A MIDSHIPMAN, THAT'S ALL.

846
00:46:17,901 --> 00:46:19,467
BUT YOU'VE ONLY
STARTED.

847
00:46:19,534 --> 00:46:21,200
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO TELL ME THAT.

848
00:46:21,267 --> 00:46:23,734
BUT IF YOU THINK I'M GOING
TO GO THROUGH 4 SOLID YEARS

849
00:46:23,801 --> 00:46:26,234
OF THIS NAVY RATTLETRAP,
YOU'RE CRAZY.

850
00:46:26,300 --> 00:46:29,434
OH, THERE, THERE,
MR. MOUNT VESUVIUS.

851
00:46:29,501 --> 00:46:31,767
AFTER THE WAY YOU
TALKED IN NEW YORK,

852
00:46:31,834 --> 00:46:34,167
I CAN'T UNDERSTAND WHY
YOU CHANGED YOUR MIND

853
00:46:34,234 --> 00:46:35,367
ABOUT THE ACADEMY.

854
00:46:35,434 --> 00:46:37,501
BUT NOW YOU'RE HERE,
IT'S DIFFERENT.

855
00:46:37,567 --> 00:46:39,267
NO, NO, IT ISN'T.

856
00:46:39,334 --> 00:46:41,901
I'M GOING TO GET OUT OF THIS
PLACE ON A GREASED SLIDE.

857
00:46:41,968 --> 00:46:44,400
WHAT DOES YOUR FATHER
SAY ABOUT THAT?

858
00:46:44,467 --> 00:46:47,300
I HAVEN'T SEEN MY DAD
UP CLOSE IN 3 MONTHS.

859
00:46:47,367 --> 00:46:50,267
NOBODY'S GOING TO SAY
I'M GREASING MY OLD MAN.

860
00:46:50,334 --> 00:46:52,267
I'M NOT GOING
TO SEE HIM, EITHER.

861
00:46:52,334 --> 00:46:53,767
I'M JUST GOING
TO CLEAR OUT.

862
00:46:53,834 --> 00:46:55,300
IT MAY BE TOUGH
TO GET IN HERE,

863
00:46:55,367 --> 00:46:57,667
BUT THEY SAY IT'S EASY
TO GET OUT IF YOU WANT TO.

864
00:46:57,734 --> 00:46:59,567
I'M JUST GOING TO
RESIGN, THAT'S ALL.

865
00:46:59,634 --> 00:47:01,367
WE CAN PICK UP
WHERE WE WERE

866
00:47:01,434 --> 00:47:03,200
BEFORE I MADE THE
MISTAKE OF COMING HERE.

867
00:47:03,267 --> 00:47:06,400
DICK... IF YOU QUIT
THE ACADEMY,

868
00:47:06,467 --> 00:47:09,534
I NEVER WANT TO SEE YOU
AGAIN AS LONG AS I LIVE.

869
00:47:09,601 --> 00:47:11,968
BUT I THOUGHT YOU WANTED
ME TO STAY OUT OF THE NAVY!

870
00:47:12,033 --> 00:47:13,300
WELL, THAT WAS TRUE.

871
00:47:13,367 --> 00:47:15,934
WE TALKED OF STARS
AND GOT A LITTLE DIZZY.

872
00:47:16,000 --> 00:47:18,000
AND WE TALKED ABOUT
MARRIAGE AND THINGS.

873
00:47:18,067 --> 00:47:20,567
BUT I'M TALKING ABOUT
YOU AND NOW.

874
00:47:20,634 --> 00:47:23,701
YOU CHOSE TO ENTER
THE ACADEMY.

875
00:47:23,767 --> 00:47:25,267
IF YOU CHOOSE
TO GO YELLOW

876
00:47:25,334 --> 00:47:27,901
ON WHAT YOU SWORE TO DO
WHEN YOU BECAME A MIDSHIPMAN-

877
00:47:27,968 --> 00:47:29,834
BUT I'M NOT GOING
YELLOW, I'M JUST QUITTING.

878
00:47:29,901 --> 00:47:32,000
IF YOU QUIT ANYTHING
YOU SWORE TO DO,

879
00:47:32,067 --> 00:47:35,100
WHETHER IT BE NAVY
OR THE NORTH POLE,

880
00:47:35,167 --> 00:47:37,634
I WOULDN'T THINK
VERY MUCH OF YOU.

881
00:47:37,701 --> 00:47:40,767
OH, YOU DON'T
MAKE SENSE.

882
00:47:40,834 --> 00:47:43,734
IF I STAY IN THE ACADEMY,
YOU WON'T MARRY ME

883
00:47:43,801 --> 00:47:45,300
BECAUSE THAT
MAKES ME A NAVY MAN.

884
00:47:45,367 --> 00:47:48,300
YOU LOST YOUR FATHER AND
BROTHER THAT WAY, IS THAT RIGHT?

885
00:47:49,267 --> 00:47:50,534
AND IF I GET OUT
OF THE ACADEMY

886
00:47:50,601 --> 00:47:53,100
NOW THAT I'M IN IT, YOU
WON'T SEE ME ANYMORE.

887
00:47:53,167 --> 00:47:54,801
IS THAT RIGHT, TOO?

888
00:47:54,868 --> 00:47:57,400
YES. THAT'S RIGHT, TOO.

889
00:48:00,701 --> 00:48:03,667
WOULD YOU MIND IF I
SAID GOOD AFTERNOON?

890
00:48:03,734 --> 00:48:06,868
I'M GOING SLOWLY AND
COMPLETELY DAFFY.

891
00:48:11,868 --> 00:48:14,400
AND THAT, SIR, IS THAT
MIDSHIPMAN'S OPINION

892
00:48:14,467 --> 00:48:16,434
OF THE UNITED STATES
NAVAL ACADEMY.

893
00:48:16,501 --> 00:48:20,300
IF YOU WERE HE, SIR, WHAT WOULD
YOU DO? STAY IN OR GET OUT?

894
00:48:20,367 --> 00:48:21,901
IF I WERE THAT BOY,

895
00:48:21,968 --> 00:48:24,300
I'D GET OUT AS FAST
AS I COULD.

896
00:48:24,367 --> 00:48:25,934
YOU WOULD, SIR?

897
00:48:26,000 --> 00:48:27,133
YES.

898
00:48:27,200 --> 00:48:29,934
BUT I DON'T KNOW OF ANY
MIDSHIPMAN IN THE ACADEMY

899
00:48:30,000 --> 00:48:32,067
ANSWERING THE DESCRIPTION
YOU'VE GIVEN ME.

900
00:48:32,133 --> 00:48:35,100
IF HE IS HERE,
HE CERTAINLY OUGHT NOT TO BE.

901
00:48:35,167 --> 00:48:37,767
BUT I DO KNOW THAT THE
BELLIGERENT YOUNG NINCOMPOOP

902
00:48:37,834 --> 00:48:40,634
YOU'VE JUST DESCRIBED
ISN'T MY SON.

903
00:48:40,701 --> 00:48:43,067
THE SPIRIT OF THE ACADEMY
INCLUDES MANY ELEMENTS

904
00:48:43,133 --> 00:48:45,334
BESIDES THE QUALITIES
OF HONOR,

905
00:48:45,400 --> 00:48:48,133
PERSONAL INTEGRITY,
AND LOYALTY TO THE SERVICE.

906
00:48:48,200 --> 00:48:50,267
IT INCLUDES
SPORTSMANSHIP-

907
00:48:50,334 --> 00:48:53,734
THE SPIRIT THAT ENABLES A MAN
TO BE ABLE TO GIVE AND TAKE.

908
00:48:53,801 --> 00:48:56,300
AND UNLESS THAT MIDSHIPMAN
CAN LEARN THAT QUALITY,

909
00:48:56,367 --> 00:48:58,701
HE MAY FIND HIMSELF
IN THE UNFORTUNATE POSITION

910
00:48:58,767 --> 00:49:02,000
OF WORKING UP THROUGH
HIS CLASSES WITH NO PALS,

911
00:49:02,067 --> 00:49:05,567
NO FRIENDS... ALONE.

912
00:49:05,634 --> 00:49:07,534
THANK YOU, SIR.

913
00:49:07,601 --> 00:49:08,901
PERHAPS THAT'S
THE COURSE

914
00:49:08,968 --> 00:49:11,100
THAT MIDSHIPMAN
MAY CHOOSE TO STEER.

915
00:49:11,167 --> 00:49:13,133
GOOD MORNING, SIR.

916
00:49:19,067 --> 00:49:20,868
MISTER?

917
00:49:20,934 --> 00:49:22,133
I'VE NOTICED
A FADING AWAY

918
00:49:22,200 --> 00:49:24,067
OF YOUR SPIRITS
OF LATE,

919
00:49:24,133 --> 00:49:26,567
AND I FEEL, MISTER, THAT
IT'S PERHAPS DUE TO THE LOSS

920
00:49:26,634 --> 00:49:28,267
OF YOUR LATE LAMENTED PUBLIC ACCLAIM.

921
00:49:28,334 --> 00:49:31,300
AND AS AN ANTIDOTE TO
THAT GRIEVOUS CONDITION,

922
00:49:31,367 --> 00:49:33,334
THE FIRST CLASSMEN ARE
WILLING TO BE GENEROUS.

923
00:49:33,400 --> 00:49:36,100
THEIR DRAGS ARE WITH
THEM IN SMOKE HALL.

924
00:49:36,167 --> 00:49:38,234
THEIR HEARTS ARE INFLAMED
AT THE VERY THOUGHT

925
00:49:38,300 --> 00:49:40,834
OF HEARING THE GOLDEN
VOICE OF PLEBE DICK MELVILLE

926
00:49:40,901 --> 00:49:42,968
SING A HEART SONG
TO THEIR LADYLOVES-

927
00:49:43,033 --> 00:49:44,801
WITH, PERHAPS,
THE VAIN HOPE

928
00:49:44,868 --> 00:49:46,868
THAT THE LADYLOVES MIGHT
BECOME AMOROUSLY AFFECTED,

929
00:49:46,934 --> 00:49:48,367
SENTIMENTALLY
INCLINED,

930
00:49:48,434 --> 00:49:51,400
AND WILLING TO WAIT FOR TWO
YEARS AFTER OUR GRADUATION

931
00:49:51,467 --> 00:49:53,834
FOR THE CONGRESSIONALLY
DELAYED NUPTIALS.

932
00:49:53,901 --> 00:49:57,601
IN OTHER WORDS,
MISTER, FOLLOW ME.

933
00:50:20,300 --> 00:50:21,734
THERE YOU ARE,
MISTER.

934
