A REAL PLEASURE.

1004
00:54:34,300 --> 00:54:35,434
Women: AW...

1005
00:54:35,501 --> 00:54:37,167
EXCUSE ME, SIR.

1006
00:54:37,234 --> 00:54:40,501
WHY DIDN'T YOU
LET HIM SING MORE?

1007
00:54:45,434 --> 00:54:48,200
WELL, LOOKS LIKE
WE LOST A ROOMMATE.

1008
00:54:48,267 --> 00:54:49,834
WHAT HAPPENED?

1009
00:54:49,901 --> 00:54:51,801
ALL I KNOW IS
HE WANTED A ROOM ALONE.

1010
00:54:51,868 --> 00:54:54,267
SAID HE WANTED TO
CONCENTRATE ON HIS STUDIES.

1011
00:54:54,334 --> 00:54:56,434
HE'S MOVED IN THAT SINGLE
ROOM DOWN THE CORRIDOR.

1012
00:54:56,501 --> 00:54:59,100
HE TOLD ME ROOMMATES WERE DESIGNED
MERELY TO SHARE THEIR ROOMS,

1013
00:54:59,167 --> 00:55:00,701
NOT THEIR THOUGHTS
AND CONVERSATIONS.

1014
00:55:02,501 --> 00:55:03,868
AS FAR AS
HE'S CONCERNED,

1015
00:55:03,934 --> 00:55:06,834
THE WHOLE CLASS CAN CONSIDER
HIM DEAF AND DUMB FROM NOW ON.

1016
00:55:06,901 --> 00:55:08,334
HE DIDN'T WANT
ANY PART OF US.

1017
00:55:08,400 --> 00:55:09,968
ALL I GOT TO SAY, BOY,

1018
00:55:10,033 --> 00:55:12,968
IS THAT HE'S GONNA
FIND IT A LONESOME ROAD.

1019
00:55:15,934 --> 00:55:18,234
Dick on radio:
* SHIPMATES STAND TOGETHER

1020
00:55:18,300 --> 00:55:19,934
* DON'T GIVE UP
THE SHIP... *

1021
00:55:20,033 --> 00:55:22,767
Announcer: THIS IS
A DICK MELVILLE RECORDING.

1022
00:55:22,834 --> 00:55:25,901
* FAIR OR STORMY WEA-

1023
00:55:55,634 --> 00:55:56,934
UH, TREE'S UP.

1024
00:55:57,000 --> 00:55:58,667
COXSWAIN'S
UNSATISFACTORY AGAIN.

1025
00:55:58,734 --> 00:56:00,601
OH, I'M NOT SCARED.

1026
00:56:00,667 --> 00:56:02,767
I'M GOING TO BEAR DOWN
FOR THOSE FINAL EXAMINATIONS.

1027
00:56:02,834 --> 00:56:03,834
I'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

1028
00:56:03,901 --> 00:56:05,267
SAY, DO YOU KNOW
WHO STANDS

1029
00:56:05,334 --> 00:56:06,567
AT THE HEAD
OF THE CLASS NOW?

1030
00:56:06,634 --> 00:56:08,100
UH-HUH.

1031
00:56:08,167 --> 00:56:10,601
DICK THE MELVILLE.

1032
00:56:10,667 --> 00:56:14,267
RIGHT. AND IF THAT'S ALL
HE'S GETTING OUT OF THE ACADEMY,

1033
00:56:14,334 --> 00:56:16,167
I HOPE HE ENJOYS IT.

1034
00:56:16,234 --> 00:56:19,033
GANG...
I'M ABOUT TO UNVEIL

1035
00:56:19,100 --> 00:56:22,000
THE MIRACLE
OF ROOM 3305.

1036
00:56:22,067 --> 00:56:25,367
Prepare yourselves
for a surprise.

1037
00:56:25,434 --> 00:56:28,100
Shh...

1038
00:56:37,501 --> 00:56:39,767
RAISED ON RADIO,

1039
00:56:39,834 --> 00:56:41,767
WEANED ON RADIO.

1040
00:56:43,167 --> 00:56:45,267
GOT TO HAVE
A RADIO...

1041
00:56:46,667 --> 00:56:47,968
GOT A RADIO!

1042
00:56:53,067 --> 00:56:55,267
ANTENNA DOWN
THE SHOWER PIPE.

1043
00:56:55,334 --> 00:56:57,067
GROUND THROUGH
THE LEG OF THE BED.

1044
00:56:57,133 --> 00:56:58,434
RADIO!

1045
00:56:59,501 --> 00:57:00,901
Where?

1046
00:57:01,801 --> 00:57:03,300
YOU GOT ME!

1047
00:57:03,367 --> 00:57:06,000
* IN THE MATTRESS

1048
00:57:06,067 --> 00:57:08,133
SPARKS, YOU'LL GET WORSE
THAN DEATH IF YOU GET CAUGHT!

1049
00:57:08,200 --> 00:57:10,167
CAUGHT?

1050
00:57:10,234 --> 00:57:12,968
YOU MAY NEED THOSE BRAINS,
SPARKS, WHEN YOU GO INTO THE FLEET.

1051
00:57:13,033 --> 00:57:14,701
GET THAT THING OUT OF THERE
AND THROW IT IN THE SEVERN!

1052
00:57:14,767 --> 00:57:16,968
YOU DON'T KNOW-

1053
00:57:20,300 --> 00:57:22,934
THOUGHT FOR A MINUTE
I HEARD A RADIO IN HERE.

1054
00:57:23,000 --> 00:57:25,234
UH... DIDYOU, SIR?

1055
00:57:25,300 --> 00:57:26,667
HMM...

1056
00:57:26,734 --> 00:57:28,567
<i>I DON'T SEE ANY RADIO.</i>

1057
00:57:28,634 --> 00:57:31,567
I DON'T SEE
HOW YOU...

1058
00:57:31,634 --> 00:57:34,100
<i>COULD, SIR.</i>

1059
00:57:34,167 --> 00:57:38,267
YES, A RADIO IS A HARD
THING TO HIDE, ISN'T IT?

1060
00:57:39,167 --> 00:57:40,601
YES, SIR.

1061
00:57:40,667 --> 00:57:43,100
YES,
INDEED, SIR.

1062
00:57:43,167 --> 00:57:46,634
WOULD HAVE SWORN
I HEARD A RADIO.

1063
00:57:49,801 --> 00:57:52,133
CARRY ON!

1064
00:57:56,000 --> 00:57:57,767
All: OH!

1065
00:57:57,834 --> 00:58:00,200
YOU GOT DYNAMITE IN YOUR
MATTRESS, SPARKS! DYNAMITE!

1066
00:58:04,501 --> 00:58:06,133
Oh.

1067
00:58:08,534 --> 00:58:10,133
I GOT ONE.
GOT WHAT?

1068
00:58:10,200 --> 00:58:11,868
A LITTLE
TECUMSEH.

1069
00:58:13,367 --> 00:58:14,601
Cowboy: HEH!

1070
00:58:14,667 --> 00:58:16,234
Sparks: AH!
WHO SHRIVELED HIM UP?

1071
00:58:16,300 --> 00:58:17,734
DON'T TALK LIKE THAT!

1072
00:58:17,801 --> 00:58:19,767
DON'T GET HIM SORE AT YOU,
OR ELSE THEY'LL BE ASKING YOU

1073
00:58:19,834 --> 00:58:21,601
TO WALK OUT THE FRONT
GATE IN CIVILIAN CLOTHES!

1074
00:58:21,667 --> 00:58:24,067
THAT FELLA'S A VERY
TOUCHY LITTLE GUY, COWBOY.

1075
00:58:24,133 --> 00:58:25,667
YOU BETTER PRAY TO
HIM FOR FORGIVENESS.

1076
00:58:25,734 --> 00:58:26,934
HEH! WHAT FOR?

1077
00:58:27,000 --> 00:58:29,067
WELL, HE'S THE GOD OF
ALL WOODEN MIDSHIPMEN.

1078
00:58:29,133 --> 00:58:31,567
IF YOU WANT TO GO THROUGH
THIS ACADEMY WITHOUT ANY GRIEF,

1079
00:58:31,634 --> 00:58:34,200
YOU BETTER START GETTING
CHUMMY WITH HIM RIGHT NOW.

1080
00:58:34,267 --> 00:58:35,701
PRAY TO HIM, COWBOY.

1081
00:58:35,767 --> 00:58:38,901
WHEN YOU GET THROUGH PRAYING FOR
YOURSELF, PUT IN A WORD FOR ME,

1082
00:58:38,968 --> 00:58:41,767
BECAUSE IF I DON'T PASS THIS TEAM,
I'M NOT GOING TO BE HERE NEXT YEAR.

1083
00:58:41,834 --> 00:58:43,767
TECUMSEH, EH? HEH HEH!

1084
00:58:43,834 --> 00:58:46,767
YOU KNOW, I'D FEEL KIND OF SILLY
PRAYING TO A THING LIKE THIS.

1085
00:58:46,834 --> 00:58:50,601
Coxswain: YEAH? A LOT OF MIDSHIPMEN
THAT ARE NOW ADMIRALS DIDN'T FEEL SO.

1086
00:58:50,667 --> 00:58:53,367
WELL... HOW DO YOU
DO IT, THEN?

1087
00:58:53,434 --> 00:58:55,234
I'LL SHOW YOU. HAVE YOU GOT ANY PENNIES?

1088
00:58:55,300 --> 00:58:57,934
PENNIES?
YEAH. HERE.

1089
00:59:00,334 --> 00:59:01,467
HERE.

1090
00:59:03,801 --> 00:59:04,934
TECUMSEH, OLD BOY,

1091
00:59:05,000 --> 00:59:06,701
EVERYTHING ISN'T
EXACTLY HUNKY-DORY

1092
00:59:06,767 --> 00:59:08,701
WITH COXSWAIN
AND COWBOY.

1093
00:59:08,767 --> 00:59:10,701
WITH ME, EITHER,
FOR THAT MATTER.

1094
00:59:10,767 --> 00:59:13,434
GIVE US A BREAK ON
THESE EXAMS, WILL YOU?

1095
00:59:13,501 --> 00:59:15,634
THE 3 OF US STARTED
TOGETHER AND...

1096
00:59:15,701 --> 00:59:18,901
THAT'S THE WAY I THINK WE
OUGHT TO FINISH UP, DON'T YOU?

1097
00:59:18,968 --> 00:59:21,234
SO DON'T BEAR DOWN
TOO HARD ON US.

1098
00:59:21,300 --> 00:59:23,334
<i>REMEMBER, YOU'VE GOT
A WOODEN HEAD, TOO.</i>

1099
00:59:23,400 --> 00:59:25,434
YOU KNOW HOW IT IS.

1100
00:59:34,601 --> 00:59:35,901
HOW'D YOU COME OUT,
COXSWAIN?

1101
00:59:35,968 --> 00:59:37,200
OK!
GOOD!

1102
00:59:37,267 --> 00:59:38,734
WELL, I GUESS I WON'T
HAVE TO GO BACK

1103
00:59:38,801 --> 00:59:40,634
TO LASSOING STEERS
FOR ANOTHER YEAR.

1104
00:59:40,701 --> 00:59:42,767
YEP. UNCLE SAM, IN
HIS INFINITE WISDOM,

1105
00:59:42,834 --> 00:59:45,701
HAS DECIDED TO KEEP 3305
INTACT FOR ANOTHER YEAR.

1106
00:59:45,767 --> 00:59:46,734
HA HA!

1107
00:59:48,300 --> 00:59:50,634
Man: YIPPEE!

1108
00:59:57,067 --> 00:59:59,100
WELL, DAD, THAT'S
ONE YEAR CHECKED OFF.

1109
00:59:59,167 --> 01:00:00,968
YES, YES.

1110
01:00:01,033 --> 01:00:03,434
<i>WHY AREN'T YOU
WITH YOUR CLASSMATES?</i>

1111
01:00:03,501 --> 01:00:04,934
OH, I DON'T KNOW.

1112
01:00:05,000 --> 01:00:07,400
SOME OF THESE TRADITIONS
SEEM LIKE HORSEPLAY TO ME.

1113
01:00:07,467 --> 01:00:09,033
THERE'S NOTHING IN
THE BOOK OF REGULATIONS

1114
01:00:09,100 --> 01:00:10,767
THAT SAYS I HAVE TO DANCE
AROUND THE HERNDON MONUMENT

1115
01:00:10,834 --> 01:00:12,200
JUST BECAUSE I PASS
PLEBE YEAR.

1116
01:00:12,267 --> 01:00:13,767
HEH!

1117
01:00:13,834 --> 01:00:16,300
YOU'RE... STUBBORN.

1118
01:00:16,367 --> 01:00:18,000
YOU'RE YOUNG,

1119
01:00:18,067 --> 01:00:20,033
AND YOU'RE WRONG.

1120
01:00:20,100 --> 01:00:22,968
SOMETIMES I WISH
I WERE ALREADY RETIRED,

1121
01:00:23,033 --> 01:00:25,067
NOT SUPERINTENDENT
OF THE ACADEMY.

1122
01:00:25,133 --> 01:00:27,567
IT WOULD PUT ME IN A BETTER
POSITION TO SPEAK TO YOU-

1123
01:00:27,634 --> 01:00:30,267
AS A FATHER,
NOT AN OFFICER.

1124
01:00:30,334 --> 01:00:31,901
BUT REMEMBER THIS-

1125
01:00:31,968 --> 01:00:33,801
I'D FAR RATHER HAVE
A SON WHO DIDN'T STAND

1126
01:00:33,868 --> 01:00:35,501
AT THE HEAD OF HIS
CLASS IN STUDIES

1127
01:00:35,567 --> 01:00:38,534
IF IT ALSO MEANS THAT HE STANDS
AT THE FOOT OF HIS CLASS...

1128
01:00:38,601 --> 01:00:40,400
IN FRIENDSHIP.

1129
01:00:40,467 --> 01:00:42,868
YOU WANTED ME TO
GRADUATE FROM THE ACADEMY

1130
01:00:42,934 --> 01:00:44,400
AND I'M GOING
TO DO IT,

1131
01:00:44,467 --> 01:00:46,801
BUT I HAVE MY OWN RIGHT TO
CHOOSE THE WAY OF DOING SO.

1132
01:00:46,868 --> 01:00:48,567
OH, SON...

1133
01:00:48,634 --> 01:00:51,033
YOU'RE TYING
YOUR OWN HANG KNOT.

1134
01:00:51,100 --> 01:00:54,100
YOU CAN'T LEAVE HERE
AND GO INTO THE NAVY

1135
01:00:54,167 --> 01:00:56,100
AND EXPECT TO SERVE
WITH FELLOW OFFICERS

1136
01:00:56,167 --> 01:00:58,267
WHOM YOU REFUSE
TO MEET AS FRIENDS.

1137
01:00:58,334 --> 01:00:59,901
I HAVE NO DESIRE
WHATSOEVER

1138
01:00:59,968 --> 01:01:02,968
TO ENTER THE NAVY
UPON GRADUATION.

1139
01:01:06,167 --> 01:01:07,934
OH.

1140
01:01:12,334 --> 01:01:14,334
I WON MY WAY
INTO THIS PLACE.

1141
01:01:14,400 --> 01:01:16,200
I HAVE A CHANCE
TO GRADUATE.

1142
01:01:16,267 --> 01:01:17,868
I HAVE THE RIGHT
TO ACCEPT OR REJECT

1143
01:01:17,934 --> 01:01:19,534
MY COMMISSION WHEN
IT'S OFFERED TO ME.

1144
01:01:19,601 --> 01:01:20,868
WELL...

1145
01:01:20,934 --> 01:01:22,868
<i>SINCE THAT IS YOUR
DECISION,</i>

1146
01:01:22,934 --> 01:01:24,868
SINCE YOU'RE WILLING
TO TAKE FROM YOUR COUNTRY

1147
01:01:24,934 --> 01:01:26,868
WITH NO THOUGHT
OF GIVING IN RETURN-

1148
01:01:26,934 --> 01:01:29,234
EVEN THOUGH IT'S YOUR
PRIVILEGE UNDER THE LAW-

1149
01:01:29,300 --> 01:01:31,968
FOR THE REMAINDER OF YOUR
CAREER HERE AS A MIDSHIPMAN,

1150
01:01:32,033 --> 01:01:36,634
I PREFER THAT YOU REGARD ME AS THE
SUPERINTENDENT OF THE NAVAL ACADEMY.

1151
01:01:39,434 --> 01:01:42,033
<i>YOU'RE NOT MY SON.</i>

1152
01:01:46,133 --> 01:01:48,767
AYE AYE, SIR.

1153
01:01:54,300 --> 01:01:55,801
Man: HELLO,
MR. MELVILLE.

1154
01:01:55,868 --> 01:01:57,534
UH, MARCELLUS,
YES, SIR?

1155
01:01:57,601 --> 01:01:58,901
IS MISS BLACKBURN
STILL IN THERE?

1156
01:01:58,968 --> 01:02:02,067
YES, SIR. SHE'S BEEN DANCING
THOSE KIDS FOR AN HOUR OR SO.

1157
01:02:02,133 --> 01:02:04,734
THANK YOU.
YOU'RE WELCOME, SIR.

1158
01:02:36,968 --> 01:02:39,067
WELL, JOE, WHAT'S
THE MATTER WITH YOU?

1159
01:02:39,133 --> 01:02:41,467
I'VE BEEN A SISSY
LONG ENOUGH!

1160
01:02:41,534 --> 01:02:43,200
OH, YOU HAVE,
HAVE YOU?

1161
01:02:43,267 --> 01:02:45,400
WELL, YOU GO OVER THERE AND SIT DOWN.

1162
01:02:45,467 --> 01:02:47,067
ALL RIGHT, CHILDREN.
COME ON.

1163
01:03:33,767 --> 01:03:35,100
HERE, WHAT'S ALL THIS?

1164
01:03:35,167 --> 01:03:36,567
WHY AREN'T YOU DANCING?

1165
01:03:36,634 --> 01:03:39,067
<i>WE'D RATHER SEE YOU DANCE,
MISS BLACKBURN.</i>

1166
01:03:39,133 --> 01:03:40,400
OH, NO, NONE OF THAT.

1167
01:03:40,467 --> 01:03:43,000
NOW, COME ON. LET'S FINISH
THIS ROUTINE. LOTS OF PEP.

1168
01:03:43,067 --> 01:03:48,300
1, 2, 3, 4.

1169
01:03:48,367 --> 01:03:49,601
JUMP!

1170
01:03:54,100 --> 01:03:55,901
OH, THAT'S FINE.
GOOD-BYE, DARLINGS.

1171
01:03:55,968 --> 01:03:57,200
THAT'S ALL FOR TODAY.

1172
01:03:57,267 --> 01:03:58,901
Children: BYE! BYE!

1173
01:03:58,968 --> 01:04:00,901
GOOD-BYE.

1174
01:04:00,968 --> 01:04:03,167
WELL, TEACHER, YOU'RE DOING A
GREAT JOB WITH THOSE CHILDREN.

1175
01:04:03,234 --> 01:04:04,567
I DON'T THINK
I'D HAVE THE PATIENCE.

1176
01:04:04,634 --> 01:04:06,234
GOOD-BYE,
MISS BLACKBURN.

1177
01:04:06,300 --> 01:04:09,367
I WON'T BE COMING TO YOUR
DANCING CLASS ANYMORE.

1178
01:04:09,434 --> 01:04:11,901
WHY, DARLING?
ARE YOU GOING AWAY?

1179
01:04:11,968 --> 01:04:15,968
WELL, DAD, MOM, AND ME GOT
ORDERS, FOR THE CHINA STATION.

1180
01:04:16,033 --> 01:04:17,234
CHINA?

1181
01:04:17,300 --> 01:04:19,033
OH, DARLING,
WE'LL MISS YOU!

1182
01:04:19,100 --> 01:04:20,534
ARE YOU GLAD YOU'RE
GOING?

1183
01:04:20,601 --> 01:04:23,534
WELL, DAD AND MOM
AND ME'S IN THE NAVY.

1184
01:04:23,601 --> 01:04:27,067
WE GOT ORDERS, SO WE'RE
GOING TO CHINA NEXT SATURDAY.

1185
01:04:27,133 --> 01:04:28,868
SO GOOD-BYE,
MISS BLACKBURN.

1186
01:04:28,934 --> 01:04:29,834
GOOD-BYE, DARLING.

1187
01:04:29,901 --> 01:04:31,300
I'LL SEND YOU
A POSTCARD.

1188
01:04:31,367 --> 01:04:32,334
THANK YOU.

1189
01:04:32,400 --> 01:04:34,467
GOOD-BYE, SIR.

1190
01:04:34,534 --> 01:04:37,200
SOMEDAY I'M GOING
TO BE A MIDSHIPMAN

1191
01:04:37,267 --> 01:04:39,100
LIKE YOU, TOO.

1192
01:04:39,167 --> 01:04:40,200
BE A GOOD BOY.

1193
01:04:40,267 --> 01:04:41,534
YES, SIR.

1194
01:04:41,601 --> 01:04:43,601
I'LL BE WITH YOU IN A MINUTE,
DICK. I WANT TO CHANGE.

1195
01:04:43,667 --> 01:04:45,067
ALL RIGHT, DEAR.

1196
01:04:48,467 --> 01:04:50,567
I'VE GOT BAD NEWS,
DICK.

1197
01:04:50,634 --> 01:04:54,033
MY UNCLE HAS BEEN PASSED
OVER IN THE LAST SELECTION.

1198
01:04:54,100 --> 01:04:56,868
HE'S AUTOMATICALLY
RETIRED.

1199
01:04:56,934 --> 01:04:58,400
THAT'S THE NAVY
FOR YOU.

1200
01:04:58,467 --> 01:05:00,701
HE SERVES 25 YEARS, AND
OVERNIGHT HE'S THROUGH.

1201
01:05:00,767 --> 01:05:03,834
THERE'S ONLY ROOM FOR SO
MANY CAPTAINS IN THE NAVY.

1202
01:05:03,901 --> 01:05:06,567
<i>SOME COMMANDERS
HAVE TO BE PASSED BY.</i>

1203
01:05:06,634 --> 01:05:08,367
WELL, ARE YOU, UH...

1204
01:05:08,434 --> 01:05:10,400
IS HE LEAVING HERE?

1205
01:05:10,467 --> 01:05:13,400
HE'LL HAVE TO START IN
AGAIN AT A CIVILIAN JOB.

1206
01:05:13,467 --> 01:05:16,067
THERE'S NOTHING
HE CAN DO IN ANNAPOLIS.

1207
01:05:16,133 --> 01:05:18,067
ARE YOU GOING WITH HIM? NO.

1208
01:05:18,133 --> 01:05:20,534
I HAVE TO START OUT
ON MY OWN, TOO.

1209
01:05:20,601 --> 01:05:21,934
WHERE?

1210
01:05:22,000 --> 01:05:24,934
WELL... ALL I KNOW
HOW TO DO IS DANCE.

1211
01:05:25,000 --> 01:05:28,133
I GUESS THAT MEANS...
NEW YORK.

1212
01:05:30,667 --> 01:05:33,100
I'LL GIVE YOU A LETTER TO
THE BOYS IN THE BAND, DARLING.

1213
01:05:33,167 --> 01:05:34,334
THEY'LL HELP YOU.

1214
01:05:34,400 --> 01:05:35,701
AH AH!

1215
01:05:35,767 --> 01:05:38,234
THERE'S THE LONE WOLF OF
BANCROFT HALL DEAD AHEAD, BOYS.

1216
01:05:38,300 --> 01:05:39,934
WHAT DO WE DO
- TURN AROUND OR GO BACK?

1217
01:05:40,000 --> 01:05:42,067
LET'S RECOGNIZE HIM AND IF HE
SPEAKS TO US, ASK HIM TO JOIN US.

1218
01:05:42,133 --> 01:05:44,100
WELL, IF HE DON'T SPEAK
TO US, WE'LL JUST SUBMERGE

1219
01:05:44,167 --> 01:05:46,234
AND GO RIGHT ON BY.

1220
01:05:46,300 --> 01:05:49,934
IT ALMOST SEEMS LIKE I'M
DESERTING YOU, DOESN'T IT?

1221
01:05:53,667 --> 01:05:56,834
HELLO.

1222
01:06:04,734 --> 01:06:07,834
Men: * O THE LIFEBOAT
CREW ARE WE *

1223
01:06:07,901 --> 01:06:10,334
* AND WE SAIL
THE STORMY SEA *

1224
01:06:10,400 --> 01:06:13,133
* DA DA DA DA DA...

1225
01:06:14,534 --> 01:06:17,400
Men: * WHOA,
THE LIFEBOAT CREW ARE WE... *

1226
01:06:17,467 --> 01:06:19,901
WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO DO
WHEN I'M GONE?

1227
01:06:19,968 --> 01:06:21,567
I DON'T KNOW.

1228
01:06:21,634 --> 01:06:23,667
OH, BUT WE'LL HAVE
SEPTEMBER LEAVE TOGETHER.

1229
01:06:23,734 --> 01:06:25,234
WE CAN HAVE A LOT
OF FUN IN NEW YORK.

1230
01:06:25,300 --> 01:06:26,968
WE'LL GO OUT IN CENTRAL
PARK AND TAKE A RIDE

1231
01:06:27,033 --> 01:06:28,400
IN ONE OF THOSE
FUNNY HORSE THINGS.

1232
01:06:28,467 --> 01:06:29,701
AND WILL WE GO
TO THE ZOO?

1233
01:06:29,767 --> 01:06:32,100
MM-HMM, THEY'VE GOT A
NEW PINK RHINOCEROS THERE.

1234
01:06:32,167 --> 01:06:33,734
AND WILL WE GO
TO THE AQUARIUM?

1235
01:06:33,801 --> 01:06:34,901
UH-HUH.
AND CONEY ISLAND?

1236
01:06:34,968 --> 01:06:36,934
SURE, AND
TO GRANT'S TOMB.

1237
01:06:37,000 --> 01:06:38,934
WE'LL HAVE A LOT
OF FUN IN NEW YORK.

1238
01:06:39,000 --> 01:06:41,434
OH, DARLING,
WHEN I GET TO NEW YORK,

1239
01:06:41,501 --> 01:06:43,434
I'M NOT GOING OUT
WITH ANYBODY.

1240
01:06:43,501 --> 01:06:46,634
<i>I'M JUST GOING
TO BE YOUR GIRL.</i>

1241
01:07:13,868 --> 01:07:16,734
STEAM EXAM'S GOING TO GET ME!
STEAM! WHO KNOWS HIS STEAM?

1242
01:07:16,801 --> 01:07:18,234
DON'T HAVE
THE TIME.

1243
01:07:18,300 --> 01:07:20,734
SAY, YOU FELLAS WANT TO SEE
ME BILGE OUT OF THE ACADEMY?

1244
01:07:20,801 --> 01:07:23,000
DOESN'T ANYBODY KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT THESE STEAM PROBLEMS?

1245
01:07:23,067 --> 01:07:24,200
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU
ASK DICK MELVILLE?

1246
01:07:24,267 --> 01:07:25,200
Man: SURE, HE'S
THE SAVVY MAN.

1247
01:07:25,267 --> 01:07:26,167
HE STANDS FIRST
IN THE CLASS.

1248
01:07:26,234 --> 01:07:27,601
HE COULD HELP YOU,
COXSWAIN.

1249
01:07:27,667 --> 01:07:29,734
THANKS.

1250
01:07:52,701 --> 01:07:54,601
TECUMSEH...

1251
01:07:54,667 --> 01:07:57,100
THEY DO A LOT OF TALKING
AROUND HERE ABOUT...

1252
01:07:57,167 --> 01:08:00,968
HOW YOU'VE HELPED DUMB GUYS
LIKE ME PASS THEIR EXAMINATIONS.

1253
01:08:01,033 --> 01:08:03,934
I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE THEY'RE KIDDING ME.

1254
01:08:04,000 --> 01:08:05,601
MAYBE THEY'RE NOT, BUT...

1255
01:08:05,667 --> 01:08:08,467
I CAN'T AFFORD
TO TAKE A CHANCE.

1256
01:08:14,033 --> 01:08:16,067
IF YOU'LL HELP ME...

1257
01:08:16,133 --> 01:08:18,934
I... WELL...

1258
01:08:19,000 --> 01:08:22,100
<i>I WON'T FORGET IT, EVER!</i>

1259
01:08:23,033 --> 01:08:24,467
AND I'LL TELL ALL
THE FELLAS

1260
01:08:24,534 --> 01:08:27,934
HOW SWELL YOU WERE
TO HELP ME WHEN I NEEDED YOU.

1261
01:08:40,133 --> 01:08:42,267
WELL, GENTLEMEN,
THE SECTION AS A WHOLE

1262
01:08:42,334 --> 01:08:44,067
DID VERY WELL ON
THE FINAL EXAMINATIONS,

1263
01:08:44,133 --> 01:08:47,400
BUT ONE OR TWO OF YOU
FAILED RATHER BADLY.

1264
01:08:47,467 --> 01:08:50,567
WITHOUT A PERFECT
RECITATION TODAY,

1265
01:08:50,634 --> 01:08:54,100
I'M AFRAID SOME OF YOU
ARE GOING TO BE LEAVING US.

1266
01:08:54,167 --> 01:08:56,601
ANY QUESTIONS?

1267
01:08:56,667 --> 01:08:58,434
DRAW YOUR SLIPS,
GENTLEMEN.

1268
01:08:58,501 --> 01:09:00,167
MAN THE BOARDS.

1269
01:09:39,901 --> 01:09:42,968
I DON'T WANT YOU TO FEEL, LAWRENCE,
BECAUSE YOU'RE LEAVING HERE,

1270
01:09:43,033 --> 01:09:45,501
THAT YOU'VE LOST ALL CHANCE
OF BECOMING AN OFFICER.

1271
01:09:45,567 --> 01:09:47,901
COMPETITION HERE
IS PRETTY STIFF,

1272
01:09:47,968 --> 01:09:51,267
AND MAYBE YOU WEREN'T
QUITE READY FOR THE ACADEMY.

1273
01:09:51,334 --> 01:09:53,434
PERHAPS YOU'RE
A LITTLE TOO YOUNG.

1274
01:09:53,501 --> 01:09:55,100
YES, SIR.

1275
01:09:55,167 --> 01:09:58,100
BUT THERE'S ONE THING
I'M CERTAIN OF, BOY-

1276
01:09:58,167 --> 01:10:00,267
YOU'VE GOT THE HEART
FOR NAVY,

1277
01:10:00,334 --> 01:10:03,434
EVEN THOUGH ACADEMICS
LICKED YOU THIS TIME.

1278
01:10:03,501 --> 01:10:06,934
AND THERE ARE SOME
MIDSHIPMEN HERE WHO...

1279
01:10:07,000 --> 01:10:09,501
HAVE THE MINDS TO MAKE
OFFICERS, BUT THEY COULD USE

1280
01:10:09,567 --> 01:10:12,267
<i>A LITTLE OF THE NAVY
THAT'S IN YOUR HEART,</i>

1281
01:10:12,334 --> 01:10:14,267
BUT...

1282
01:10:14,334 --> 01:10:16,200
THAT'S THE WAY IT GOES.

1283
01:10:16,267 --> 01:10:20,067
WHAT DO YOU INTEND TO DO
AFTER YOU LEAVE HERE?

1284
01:10:21,267 --> 01:10:23,901
WELL, I'M GOING BACK
INTO THE NAVY, SIR.

1285
01:10:23,968 --> 01:10:25,801
WHETHER I CAN GIVE
COMMANDS OR TAKE THEM,

1286
01:10:25,868 --> 01:10:27,968
IT'S THE NAVY
FOR ME, SIR.

1287
01:10:28,033 --> 01:10:30,234
WELL, YOU'RE STILL
WITHIN THE AGE LIMIT.

1288
01:10:30,300 --> 01:10:34,167
YOU STILL HAVE A CHANCE TO WIN YOUR
WAY BACK HERE AND START OVER AGAIN.

1289
01:10:34,234 --> 01:10:38,734
SO, GOOD-BYE
AND GOOD LUCK TO YOU...

1290
01:10:38,801 --> 01:10:42,934
AND I HOPE THAT WE'LL
BE SHIPMATES SOMEDAY.

1291
01:10:46,300 --> 01:10:48,767
THANK YOU, SIR.

1292
01:10:55,167 --> 01:10:57,100
HELLO, COXSWAIN.

1293
01:10:57,167 --> 01:10:59,767
I JUST WANT TO...
TELL YOU HOW SORRY I AM,

1294
01:10:59,834 --> 01:11:01,767
ABOUT YOUR LEAVING
THE ACADEMY.

1295
01:11:01,834 --> 01:11:03,834
I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL.

1296
01:11:05,033 --> 01:11:07,100
DO YOU MEAN TO TELL ME
YOU KNOW HOW I FEEL?

1297
01:11:07,167 --> 01:11:08,667
<i>DO YOU?</i>

1298
01:11:08,734 --> 01:11:11,467
THE ACADEMY'S NEVER MEANT
ANYTHING TO YOU, AND IT NEVER WILL!

1299
01:11:11,534 --> 01:11:14,601
YOU'RE GOING THROUGH YOUR STUDIES
LIKE GREASED LIGHTNING AND FOR WHAT?

1300
01:11:14,667 --> 01:11:16,934
SO YOU CAN TURN DOWN YOUR
COMMISSION WHEN YOU GRADUATE!

1301
01:11:17,000 --> 01:11:20,701
DON'T YOU TRY TO TALK TO ME
ABOUT WHAT THE ACADEMY MEANS.

1302
01:11:20,767 --> 01:11:23,033
SAVE YOUR SYMPATHY
FOR SOMEBODY ELSE.

1303
01:11:23,100 --> 01:11:26,400
FORGET YOU EVER WASTED
ANY ON ME.

1304
01:11:32,934 --> 01:11:34,734
I CALL IT
DARN BAD LUCK.

1305
01:11:34,801 --> 01:11:36,934
NICE KID.

1306
01:11:37,968 --> 01:11:39,033
HI, FELLA!

1307
01:11:39,100 --> 01:11:41,234
COWBOY BROUGHT
YOUR BAG UP.

1308
01:11:41,300 --> 01:11:42,968
THANKS, COWBOY.

1309
01:11:43,033 --> 01:11:44,234
IT'S OK, KID.

1310
01:11:44,300 --> 01:11:46,567
THE SUPERINTENDENT
HAVE ANYTHING TO SAY?

1311
01:11:46,634 --> 01:11:48,033
YEAH.

1312
01:11:48,100 --> 01:11:50,400
HE SAID HE HOPED WE'D
BE SHIPMATES SOMEDAY.

1313
01:11:50,467 --> 01:11:51,901
THAT'S SWELL.

1314
01:11:51,968 --> 01:11:54,067
WE HOPE THAT, TOO.

1315
01:11:54,133 --> 01:11:55,767
SURE.

1316
01:11:57,033 --> 01:11:58,567
GEE, COXSWAIN, WOULDN'T IT
BE FUNNY IF WE WERE

1317
01:11:58,634 --> 01:12:00,434
TO COME ABOARD YOUR SHIP
AS ENSIGNS SOMEDAY

1318
01:12:00,501 --> 01:12:03,267
AND YOU HAD TO SAY,
"YES, SIR" TO-

1319
01:12:08,968 --> 01:12:11,400
HEH HEH! YEAH.

1320
01:12:11,467 --> 01:12:14,734
<i>I'D LIKE TO SEE YOU TWO GUYS
TRY TO GIVE ME ORDERS.</i>

1321
01:12:14,801 --> 01:12:16,434
FUNNY!

1322
01:12:16,501 --> 01:12:18,767
<i>IT WON'T MAKE ME
LAUGH, KID.</i>

1323
01:12:18,834 --> 01:12:21,901
I HATE
TO SEE YOU GO.

1324
01:12:26,400 --> 01:12:29,567
THAT KIND OF GOES
FOR ME, TOO.

1325
01:12:32,767 --> 01:12:36,367
REMEMBER HOW TOUGH IT WAS
TO STOW THOSE LOCKERS?

1326
01:12:36,434 --> 01:12:40,767
YOU KNOW HOW DUMB WE WERE, TOO,
COXSWAIN, AND YOU HAD TO HELP US?

1327
01:12:43,133 --> 01:12:46,300
WELL, AT... LEAST
IT WILL BE EASIER

1328
01:12:46,367 --> 01:12:47,734
GETTING YOUR STUFF OUT
THAN IT WAS

1329
01:12:47,801 --> 01:12:49,868
GETTING IT IN,
WON'T IT?

1330
01:12:49,934 --> 01:12:52,067
YEAH.

1331
01:12:57,267 --> 01:13:01,067
I GUESS I BETTER START
PACKING NOW, SPARKS.

1332
01:13:06,300 --> 01:13:09,167
I GUESS I BETTER BE
ALONE FOR A LITTLE WHILE.

1333
01:13:10,834 --> 01:13:14,901
DON'T WANT YOU TO SEE ME
MAKE A JACKASS OF MYSELF.

1334
01:14:36,434 --> 01:14:37,868
OH, MR. MELVILLE!

1335
01:14:37,934 --> 01:14:39,434
HELLO, SUSIE.
I'M GLAD TO SEE YOU.

1336
01:14:39,501 --> 01:14:41,367
GLAD TO SEE YOU, TOO. WE
SURE MISS YOU AROUND HERE.

1337
01:14:41,434 --> 01:14:43,067
YOU KNOW, YOU LOOK
YOUNGER THAN EVER?

1338
01:14:43,133 --> 01:14:45,501
<i>THE NAVY HASN'T CHANGED
YOUR LINE ANY, BUT I LOVE IT!</i>

1339
01:14:45,567 --> 01:14:46,868
HELLO, MR. MELVILLE!

1340
01:14:46,934 --> 01:14:48,534
HI, MABEL!

1341
01:14:48,601 --> 01:14:49,734
HELLO,
MR. MELVILLE!

1342
01:14:49,801 --> 01:14:51,901
HELLO, JIMMY!
HOW ARE YOU?

1343
01:14:51,968 --> 01:14:53,234
BOO!

1344
01:14:53,300 --> 01:14:55,734
MR. MELVILLE! HAVE YOU QUIT THE NAVY?

1345
01:14:55,801 --> 01:14:57,234
ARE YOU BACK
WITH US FOR GOOD?

1346
01:14:57,300 --> 01:14:59,400
NO, NO. I'M JUST HERE
ON A LITTLE LEAVE.

1347
01:14:59,467 --> 01:15:01,167
IT WAS NICE TO SEE YOU.
NICE TO SEE YOU, TOO.

1348
01:15:01,234 --> 01:15:02,667
DICK!
HELLO, HARRY.

1349
01:15:02,734 --> 01:15:04,334
WELCOME HOME! HOW DO
THEY LIKE JUNE HERE?

1350
01:15:04,400 --> 01:15:05,567
HOW DO THEY
LIKE HER?

1351
01:15:05,634 --> 01:15:06,667
COME ON OVER HERE
AND SIT DOWN.

1352
01:15:06,734 --> 01:15:08,901
OH, BOY, THE OLD PLACE
LOOKS JUST THE SAME.

1353
01:15:08,968 --> 01:15:10,534
UH-HUH. YOU CAN FORGET
THE COVER CHARGE.

1354
01:15:10,601 --> 01:15:12,100
I'LL DO THAT.
I'M A SCHOOLBOY NOW.

1355
01:15:12,167 --> 01:15:13,567
I ONLY MAKE
$3.00 A MONTH.

1356
01:16:33,834 --> 01:16:35,033
HELLO, SWEETHEART.

1357
01:16:35,100 --> 01:16:36,667
OH, DICK!
HOW ARE YOU?

1358
01:16:36,734 --> 01:16:37,667
OH, YOU'RE A SIGHT
FOR SORE-

1359
01:16:39,334 --> 01:16:40,767
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

1360
01:16:40,834 --> 01:16:42,767
DICK MELVILLE IS HERE
IN THE SKY CLUB TONIGHT.

1361
01:16:42,834 --> 01:16:43,934
LET'S HAVE HIM SING!

1362
01:16:46,667 --> 01:16:48,701
COME ON, DICK, A SONG-
FOR OLD TIMES' SAKE.

1363
01:16:48,767 --> 01:16:50,200
NO, HARRY. THEY DON'T
WANT TO HEAR ME SING.

1364
01:16:50,267 --> 01:16:52,467
YES, THEY DO.
COME ON.

1365
01:17:05,033 --> 01:17:07,167
* JUST A GLANCE

1366
01:17:07,234 --> 01:17:08,834
* AT A DANCE

1367
01:17:08,901 --> 01:17:12,334
* AND IN MY HEART I KNEW

1368
01:17:12,400 --> 01:17:15,701
* THAT IF I EVER SHOULD CARE

1369
01:17:15,767 --> 01:17:19,767
* THAT I WOULD CARE FOR YOU

1370
01:17:19,834 --> 01:17:21,601
* THOUGH I HEARD

1371
01:17:21,667 --> 01:17:23,067
* NOT A WORD

1372
01:17:23,133 --> 01:17:26,067
* YOUR EYES BEGAN TO SAY

1373
01:17:26,133 --> 01:17:30,934
* A LOT OF THINGS YOUR LIPS
HAVE NEVER TOLD ME *

1374
01:17:31,000 --> 01:17:35,801
* TO THIS VERY DAY

1375
01:17:35,868 --> 01:17:39,801
* EVERY TIME YOUR LIPS
SAY, "NO, SIR" *

1376
01:17:39,868 --> 01:17:44,033
* I WON'T LISTEN, I'M TOO WISE

1377
01:17:44,100 --> 01:17:46,968
* I WOULD RATHER LISTEN

1378
01:17:47,033 --> 01:17:50,434
* TO YOUR EYES

1379
01:17:52,167 --> 01:17:56,234
* THEY HAVE TOLD ME
LOTS OF THINGS, DEAR *

1380
01:17:56,300 --> 01:18:00,300
* THAT YOUR BETTER SELF DENIES

1381
01:18:00,367 --> 01:18:03,467
* SO I'D RATHER LISTEN

1382
01:18:03,534 --> 01:18:06,868
* TO THOSE EYES

1383
01:18:06,934 --> 01:18:10,300
* THERE'S NOTHING
YOU COULD EVER SAY *

1384
01:18:10,367 --> 01:18:12,334
* THAT COULD CONVEY

1385
01:18:12,400 --> 01:18:15,267
* THE PROMISE
I'VE BEEN WAITING FOR *

1386
01:18:15,334 --> 01:18:16,300
COME ON.

1387
01:18:16,367 --> 01:18:18,534
* I LOOK IN YOUR EYES

1388
01:18:18,601 --> 01:18:20,767
* AND REALIZE

1389
01:18:20,834 --> 01:18:24,267
* THEY CAN TELL ME MORE

1390
01:18:24,334 --> 01:18:28,234
* EYES CAN BE SINCERE
AND TRUTHFUL *

1391
01:18:28,300 --> 01:18:32,434
* LIPS CAN TELL
A LOT OF LIES *

1392
01:18:32,501 --> 01:18:35,100
* SO I'D RATHER LISTEN

1393
01:18:35,167 --> 01:18:44,100
* TO YOUR EYES

1394
01:18:52,300 --> 01:18:55,100
MIDSHIPMAN MELVILLE, SECOND
CLASS, REPORTING, SIR.

1395
01:18:55,167 --> 01:18:56,968
COME IN.

1396
01:18:59,300 --> 01:19:02,267
MELVILLE... I THINK IT
WOULD BE BETTER FOR YOU

1397
01:19:02,334 --> 01:19:04,067
AND FOR THE SPIRIT OF
YOUR COMPANY IN GENERAL

1398
01:19:04,133 --> 01:19:06,767
IF YOU SHARED A ROOM WITH SOME
OF YOUR CLASSMATES THIS YEAR.

1399
01:19:06,834 --> 01:19:08,901
YOU STAND FIRST
IN YOUR CLASS,

1400
01:19:08,968 --> 01:19:10,400
YOU'VE KEPT OFF
THE REPORT,

1401
01:19:10,467 --> 01:19:12,901
BUT YOUR APTITUDE- FOR-SERVICE
RECORD IS NOTHING TO BE PROUD OF.

1402
01:19:12,968 --> 01:19:15,234
DO YOU KNOW WHY?

1403
01:19:16,300 --> 01:19:17,901
YOU'RE NOT IN
A COLLEGE, MELVILLE.

1404
01:19:17,968 --> 01:19:20,067
THE ACADEMY IS MORE
THAN THAT.

1405
01:19:20,133 --> 01:19:22,968
AT A UNIVERSITY, YOU COULD GO
YOUR OWN WAY AND DO AS YOU PLEASE.

1406
01:19:23,033 --> 01:19:25,000
WITH YOUR SCHOLASTIC
RECORD, YOU'D GRADUATE,

1407
01:19:25,067 --> 01:19:26,501
PROBABLY WITH GREAT
DISTINCTION.

1408
01:19:26,567 --> 01:19:28,167
THEN YOUR COLLEGE
PRESIDENT WOULD SEND FOR YOU

1409
01:19:28,234 --> 01:19:30,200
TO WISH YOU GOOD-BYE AND
GOOD LUCK. YOU'D LEAVE.

1410
01:19:30,267 --> 01:19:33,734
THE COLLEGE WOULD CEASE
TO BE A PART OF YOUR LIFE.

1411
01:19:33,801 --> 01:19:36,367
IT'S DIFFERENT HERE.

1412
01:19:36,434 --> 01:19:40,767
WHEN A MIDSHIPMAN LEAVES, WE
ALWAYS SAY, "GOOD-BYE, GOOD LUCK...

1413
01:19:40,834 --> 01:19:44,267
AND I HOPE WE'LL
BE SHIPMATES SOMEDAY."

1414
01:19:44,334 --> 01:19:47,434
WHO ARE YOUR FRIENDS
IN YOUR CLASS?

1415
01:19:47,501 --> 01:19:49,300
I HAVE NONE, SIR.

1416
01:19:49,367 --> 01:19:51,133
WHY NOT?

1417
01:19:51,200 --> 01:19:53,467
IT WAS MY OWN
CHOICE, SIR.

1418
01:19:53,534 --> 01:19:55,734
I THOUGHT THAT, SINCE
I DIDN'T INTEND...

1419
01:19:55,801 --> 01:19:57,467
TO BE SHIPMATES
WITH MY CLASSMATES

1420
01:19:57,534 --> 01:19:59,801
THAT PERHAPS FRIENDSHIP
WASN'T NECESSARY.

1421
01:19:59,868 --> 01:20:02,367
<i>WHAT YOU INTEND TO DO IN REGARD
TO THE ACCEPTANCE OR REJECTION</i>

1422
01:20:02,434 --> 01:20:04,567
OF YOUR COMMISSION IS NOT
MY BUSINESS. IT'S YOURS.

1423
01:20:04,634 --> 01:20:06,334
WHAT YOUR LIFE
IS HERE MUST-

1424
01:20:06,400 --> 01:20:08,601
<i>BECAUSE OF THE NATURE OF
THINGS-BE PART OF MY BUSINESS.</i>

1425
01:20:08,667 --> 01:20:10,968
YOU'RE FAILING COMPLETELY IN
ONE THING THE ACADEMY HAS TO GIVE

1426
01:20:11,033 --> 01:20:13,334
TO A VERY GREAT
DEGREE-FRIENDSHIP.

1427
01:20:13,400 --> 01:20:17,234
NOW, YOU'VE HAD TWO YEARS TO DO SOMETHING
ABOUT THIS ON YOUR OWN, MELVILLE.

1428
01:20:17,300 --> 01:20:21,567
IT'S TIME YOU CHECKED ON YOUR
COMPASS AND CHARTED A NEW COURSE.

1429
01:20:21,634 --> 01:20:24,601
YOU SAY YOU HAVE
NO FRIENDS HERE.

1430
01:20:24,667 --> 01:20:27,334
WHOM DO YOU TRUST
AMONGST YOUR CLASSMATES?

1431
01:20:27,400 --> 01:20:29,434
BROWN, LINCOLN,

1432
01:20:29,501 --> 01:20:31,567
EVEN TED STERLING,

1433
01:20:31,634 --> 01:20:33,567
<i>BUT THEY HAVE NO REASON
TO LIKE ME, SIR.</i>

1434
01:20:33,634 --> 01:20:34,934
PERHAPS NOT.

1435
01:20:35,000 --> 01:20:37,601
MAYBE THEY HAVEN'T
BEEN GIVEN A CHANCE.

1436
01:20:37,667 --> 01:20:39,667
THEY MAY BE YOUR
NEW ROOMMATES.

1437
01:20:39,734 --> 01:20:40,934
YOU MAY GO NOW.

1438
01:20:41,000 --> 01:20:42,634
YES, SIR.

1439
01:20:43,968 --> 01:20:46,234
THIRD BATTALION, PLEASE.

1440
01:20:46,300 --> 01:20:48,000
THIS IS CAPTAIN DOUGLAS.

1441
01:20:48,067 --> 01:20:51,601
I WANT TO SEE MIDSHIPMEN
BROWN, LINCOLN, AND STERLING.

1442
01:20:54,667 --> 01:20:56,767
RADIO SOUNDS
MIGHTY GOOD,

1443
01:20:56,834 --> 01:20:58,467
RIGHT OUT IN
THE OPEN LIKE THIS.

1444
01:20:58,534 --> 01:21:00,634
Cowboy: SOUNDS BETTER THAN IT
DID IN YOUR MATTRESS, DOESN'T IT?

1445
01:21:00,701 --> 01:21:02,467
HA HA!

1446
01:21:02,534 --> 01:21:04,033
YOU KNOW, DICK,

1447
01:21:04,100 --> 01:21:07,133
<i>I HAD A RADIO IN MY
MATTRESS WHEN I WAS A PLEBE.</i>

1448
01:21:07,200 --> 01:21:08,200
YOU DID?

1449
01:21:08,267 --> 01:21:10,300
YEAH. SURE DID.

1450
01:21:10,367 --> 01:21:12,367
HI, FELLAS. SAW
A LETTER FOR YOU.

1451
01:21:12,434 --> 01:21:13,334
THOUGHT I'D
BRING IT OVER.

1452
01:21:13,400 --> 01:21:14,601
I RECOGNIZED
THE HANDWRITING.

1453
01:21:14,667 --> 01:21:16,400
IT'S FROM OUR GIRLFRIEND. THANKS, TED.

1454
01:21:16,467 --> 01:21:19,934
OH, ANYTHING FOR A
ROOMMATE, I ALWAYS SAYS.

1455
01:22:22,133 --> 01:22:24,100
Man: HOORAY!

1456
01:22:36,467 --> 01:22:38,100
OH HO! HEH!

1457
01:22:38,167 --> 01:22:40,267
IT AIN'T PRIVATE
ENOUGH HERE.

1458
01:22:42,467 --> 01:22:45,200
THEY'RE MARCHING
THROUGH THE RING, DICK.

1459
01:22:45,267 --> 01:22:47,567
LET'S GO BACK
AND GET IN LINE.

1460
01:22:47,634 --> 01:22:51,067
DARLING, I CAN'T WAIT
TO PUT THIS RING ON YOU.

1461
01:22:52,334 --> 01:22:54,400
LET'S SKIP IT,
DO YOU MIND?

1462
01:22:54,467 --> 01:22:56,601
I'D BE AWFULLY UNCOMFORTABLE UP THERE,

1463
01:22:56,667 --> 01:22:57,968
REALLY I WOULD.

1464
01:22:59,501 --> 01:23:01,434
OH, COME ON!

1465
01:23:01,501 --> 01:23:03,434
I'M GOING ON MY
LAST CRUISE TOMORROW.

1466
01:23:03,501 --> 01:23:06,434
LET'S DON'T WASTE TIME
WALKING THROUGH A RING.

1467
01:23:06,501 --> 01:23:09,167
I WON'T SEE YOU
FOR 3 LONG MONTHS.

1468
01:23:09,234 --> 01:23:11,100
WHY DID YOU PUT YOUR
RING IN YOUR POCKET?

1469
01:23:11,167 --> 01:23:12,767
WHY DON'T
YOU WEAR IT?

1470
01:23:12,834 --> 01:23:15,100
OH, THERE ARE ABOUT
450 CLASSMATES UP THERE

1471
01:23:15,167 --> 01:23:16,801
WHO WOULD RATHER
I WOULDN'T WEAR IT.

1472
01:23:16,868 --> 01:23:19,400
BUT YOU WROTE ME THAT YOU WERE
MIXING WITH YOUR CLASSMATES.

1473
01:23:19,467 --> 01:23:20,868
I'M TRYING TO,
BUT...

1474
01:23:20,934 --> 01:23:22,901
IT'S A LITTLE
TOUGH ON THEM.

1475
01:23:22,968 --> 01:23:24,534
I GUESS I JUST
DON'T FIT.

1476
01:23:24,601 --> 01:23:27,067
DARLING, WHAT ARE YOU
GOING TO DO ON THE CRUISE?

1477
01:23:27,133 --> 01:23:29,400
I DON'T KNOW, BUT LET'S
DON'T TALK ABOUT IT.

1478
01:23:29,467 --> 01:23:31,234
ALL I WANT TO DO
IS BE WITH YOU.

1479
01:23:31,300 --> 01:23:32,934
OH, DARLING!

1480
01:23:35,300 --> 01:23:36,901
Officer: I'M LOOKING
FOR MELVILLE.

1481
01:23:36,968 --> 01:23:37,901
YES, SIR.

1482
01:23:37,968 --> 01:23:39,901
I WANT BROWN,
LINCOLN, AND STERLING.

1483
01:23:39,968 --> 01:23:42,300
YES, SIR. BROWN, LINCOLN, STERLING!

1484
01:23:44,567 --> 01:23:46,434
HAVE YOU GOT ALL THE GEAR
YOU'RE REQUIRED TO HAVE HERE?

1485
01:23:46,501 --> 01:23:47,601
YES, SIR.

1486
01:23:47,667 --> 01:23:48,934
ALL RIGHT,
SIGN UP ON THIS LIST.

1487
01:23:49,000 --> 01:23:50,167
YES, SIR.

1488
01:23:55,167 --> 01:23:58,434
OH, I WAS SCARED. I THOUGHT
I WASN'T GOING TO FIND YOU.

1489
01:23:58,501 --> 01:24:00,234
WELL, HERE WE ARE.

1490
01:24:01,634 --> 01:24:05,100
OH, DICK, I HAVE SUCH A
STRANGE FEELING IN MY HEART.

1491
01:24:05,167 --> 01:24:07,100
MINE ISN'T EXACTLY
JUMPING FOR JOY.

1492
01:24:07,167 --> 01:24:09,434
I DON'T MEAN THAT. I
MEAN ABOUT THE CRUISE

1493
01:24:09,501 --> 01:24:11,567
AND WHAT IT'S GOING
TO MEAN TO YOU.

1494
01:24:11,634 --> 01:24:13,901
IT JUST MEANS THAT
I'M TRADING THIS JAIL

1495
01:24:13,968 --> 01:24:15,567
FOR A FLOATING ONE,
THAT'S ALL.

1496
01:24:15,634 --> 01:24:17,868
YOU'VE MADE UP YOUR MIND
TO HATE IT, HAVEN'T YOU?

1497
01:24:17,934 --> 01:24:21,901
NO. IT'S JUST GOING TO BE ONE
LONG, LOVELY YACHTING TRIP.

1498
01:24:21,968 --> 01:24:25,067
HAVE YOU SAID GOOD-BYE TO YOUR FATHER?

1499
01:24:25,133 --> 01:24:27,400
NO.

1500
01:24:27,467 --> 01:24:29,601
I DON'T THINK
HE EXPECTED IT.

1501
01:24:32,667 --> 01:24:35,234
YOUR SON LEADS HIS CLASS
AGAIN THIS YEAR, SIR.

1502
01:24:35,300 --> 01:24:36,901
CONGRATULATIONS
ARE IN ORDER.

1503
01:24:36,968 --> 01:24:39,901
I KNOW WHERE HE STANDS, EVEN
THOUGH IT'S NOT ALL ON THE RECORD.

1504
01:24:39,968 --> 01:24:41,868
AND I KNOW THAT
YOU KNOW, DOUGLAS.

1505
01:24:41,934 --> 01:24:43,868
PERHAPS HE'LL GET HIS
BEARINGS ON THIS CRUISE.

1506
01:24:43,934 --> 01:24:45,901
HE'LL HAVE A CHANCE
TO FIND HIMSELF.

1507
01:24:45,968 --> 01:24:48,901
THIS CRUISE IS GOING TO
MAKE OR BREAK THAT BOY.

1508
01:24:48,968 --> 01:24:52,300
THIS IS HIS LAST CHANCE
TO PROVE HIS COURSE.

1509
01:24:52,367 --> 01:24:54,934
AM I ALL YOU'VE GOT TO
SAY GOOD-BYE TO, DICK?

1510
01:24:55,000 --> 01:24:57,067
LET'S JUST MAKE IT
"YOU'RE ALL I'VE GOT."

1511
01:24:57,133 --> 01:24:58,334
THAT COVERS EVERYTHING.

1512
01:24:58,400 --> 01:25:00,534
Sparks: WELL! IF IT ISN'T
LITTLE JUNE AND BIG RICHARD.

1513
01:25:00,601 --> 01:25:01,634
Cowboy: MIND IF
WE CRASH HERE?

1514
01:25:01,701 --> 01:25:02,734
WHY, SURE I'D-

1515
01:25:02,801 --> 01:25:05,100
YOU SEE, MY FOLKS ARE
ARKANSAS HILLBILLIES,

1516
01:25:05,167 --> 01:25:07,734
AND HIS FOLKS HAD TO MILK
THE STEERS IN ARIZONA.

1517
01:25:07,801 --> 01:25:09,100
WHOA, YOU
DARN FOOL.

1518
01:25:09,167 --> 01:25:10,601
YOU CAN'T
MILK A STEER.

1519
01:25:10,667 --> 01:25:12,601
YOU OUGHT TO
COME TO ARKANSAS.

1520
01:25:12,667 --> 01:25:15,434
WE CROSS OUR STEERS WITH
GOATS, AND THEY MILK FINE.

1521
01:25:16,968 --> 01:25:18,434
WHAT SPARKY'S
TRYING TO SAY IS

1522
01:25:18,501 --> 01:25:20,067
THAT SINCE
WE FELLAS HAVE

1523
01:25:20,133 --> 01:25:22,968
NO FOLKS OF OUR OWN HERE
TO SAY GOOD-BYE TO US,

1524
01:25:23,033 --> 01:25:26,601
WE MIGHT AS WELL SAY
GOOD-BYE TO EACH OTHER.

1525
01:25:26,667 --> 01:25:28,133
OH, I SEE.

1526
01:25:28,200 --> 01:25:31,467
WELL, I-AH-GUESS
IT WON'T BE LONG NOW.

1527
01:25:31,534 --> 01:25:33,467
YEAH, I-I GUESS
WE MIGHT AS WELL

1528
01:25:33,534 --> 01:25:35,634
GET DOWN TO THIS KISSING
BUSINESS RIGHT NOW.

1529
01:25:35,701 --> 01:25:36,801
HOW'S ABOUT IT,
SWEETIE?

1530
01:25:36,868 --> 01:25:39,267
READY AND WAITING, SIR.

1531
01:25:39,334 --> 01:25:42,934
LOOKS LIKE WE CAN'T DO IT
IN PRIVATE THIS TIME, KID.

1532
01:25:43,000 --> 01:25:44,968
KIND OF LOOKS
LIKE THAT, COWBOY.

1533
01:25:45,033 --> 01:25:48,467
WELL, LET'S GET
AT IT THEN, HUH?

1534
01:25:48,534 --> 01:25:51,133
WELL, I GUESS
WE MIGHT AS WELL.

1535
01:25:53,300 --> 01:25:55,367
I FEEL AWFULLY
EMPTY, DICK.

1536
01:25:55,434 --> 01:25:58,300
I'LL BE BACK
IN 3 MONTHS.

1537
01:25:58,367 --> 01:26:00,467
WILL YOU BE
DIFFERENT THEN?

1538
01:26:00,534 --> 01:26:02,067
DO YOU WANT ME TO BE?

1539
01:26:02,133 --> 01:26:06,133
IN A WAY I MEAN YES,
WITH ALL MY HEART.

1540
01:26:06,200 --> 01:26:10,501
<i>I'M-
I WAS A NAVY GIRL.</i>

1541
01:26:10,567 --> 01:26:15,434
I'VE SAID GOOD-BYE LIKE
THIS TO DAD, JIMMY...

1542
01:26:15,501 --> 01:26:16,968
BUT IT'S DIFFERENT
WITH YOU.

1543
01:26:17,033 --> 01:26:20,601
BUT NAVY WAS THEIR
LIFE, DARLING.

1544
01:26:20,667 --> 01:26:23,767
DON'T LISTEN TO ME.

1545
01:26:23,834 --> 01:26:25,601
MAYBE THAT'S
WHAT I MEAN.

1546
01:26:25,667 --> 01:26:28,167
<i>MAYBE I WANT NAVY TO BE YOUR LIFE.</i>

1547
01:26:30,367 --> 01:26:31,467
